column13: best pre-shave oil on the market!
column14: I have been using this product for several years now.  I shave my face and head.  My shaving ritual - rinse head & face with hot water, apply shave secret, barbasol.  After shaving, finish with alum bar and and moisturize with coconut oil (don't knock it! I have eczema - it's very gentle, & far cheaper and more luxurious than any after shave moisturizer out there!)  For me, this product is terrible as a stand alone shaving cream.  Where this product shines is as a pre-shave oil. You can feel the menthol, which is just right.  I found that the # of drops recommended to be too conservative.  I use 8 drops to shave my head and 6 drops to shave my face.  Even at that, this product lasts.  I definitely notice that razor burn occurs far less frequently.  In fact, I can't even remember when I last had razor burn.  I recommend finishing your shave with an alum bar.  When I forget to use this oil, I definitely notice when I finish with the alum bar (it burns!) - so I do know this product isn't crap.  It's also a good practice to use the alum bar because it serves as a good indicator for when you need to replace your razor blade.  Try it!

column6: La Magie Hair Organic Fast Growth Serum Get Long, Beautiful Hair~First Organic Hair Serum, Now with anti Frizz
column13: Hair Growth Spa Treatment Has Stopped My Hair Loss In It's Tracks!
column14:
I haven't been using this long enough to see if my hair is really growing back, but what I do know, is it has drastically reduced the amount of hair I am losing every time I shower or brush it. My mother's hair got pretty thin after she turned 40, and I just hit that age 6 months ago. It seems like over the past 3 to 4 months, my hair has been falling out like crazy. Every time I brush my hair, I have to clean my brush out because I am experiencing tremendous hair loss. I am devastated by how thin my hair has become.

I ordered this a few week ago, in the 30ml size. I am so glad it is made of 100% Natural and Organic Essential Oils. I don't want to put harsh chemicals on my scalp. After using this for the first week, I started to notice my hair wasn't falling out with reckless abandon like it was just days before. After another week, I feel like I am losing the same amount of hair as before, which has essentially knocked out the shedding that has been making me self conscious for the past several months. I haven't used it long enough to know if regrowth is under way, but I do know the excessive shedding has stopped, dead in it's tracks, and this is the only thing I am using right now for hair loss prevention and growth restoration.

It's easy to apply, I just put it on my dry hair, after I brush it, and leave it in for at least 20 minutes before I get in the shower. This way, my hair isn't oily after using it. This is the method of application La Magie recommends, so I am sticking to the directions. I rub and massage, very gently, a small amount, into my scalp and do a chore or two while waiting the full 20 minutes. It also smells wonderful and I am so happy I was chosen to receive this at a great, promotional price, in exchange for my honest, unbiased opinion and feedback. This is my personal experience with this product. This is also another reason why I secretly want to smack my husband. He has a perfectly thick head of hair with no hair loss at all, and neither does his father! Tsk Tsk Tsk!th no hair loss at all, and neither does his father! Tsk Tsk Tsk!

column13: It seems less dull, fine lines aren't as visible
column14: I have purchased this product three times and I do see a difference in my skin. It seems less dull, fine lines aren't as visible, and the couple of age spots I had are barely visible now. Also, I had a broken blood vessel (I don't think that's technically the correct term, but it looked like a red dot on my cheek that I always felt compelled to cover up) which you can hardly see at all now. My step-mother always used to tell me I looked tired, but she rarely says that to me now (thank God!) I think it's reasonably priced and it lasts a long time if you follow directions. I'm 53, but I would tell younger women who don't have wrinkles or age spots yet to use this now! Don't wait!

column6: AXE Phoenix Special Edition Triple Pack 24H Anti-Perspirant & Deodorant 2.7oz each with BONUS
column13: NOT the same antiperspirant AND deodorant product
column14:
I believe Axe has changed this product because it's getting increasingly difficult to find the sticks that say both ANTIPERSPIRANT AND DEODORANT. The photo and description for this item indicate that it is both but what I received was a different product that says only ANTIPERSPIRANT on it. The only reason I ordered these was because I thought it was the older product that is indeed both antiperspirant and deodorant in one. I know that the active ingredient is the same on both products but the sticks that still have "ANTIPERSPIRANT AND DEODORANT" on the packaging and product apply differently (they feel different) and they do not cake up or get sticky. I do not like the current version of this product that has apparently phased out its predecessor. I also cannot seem to find the ANT and DEOD product in stores anymore or at any of the locations I used to be able to buy it at. Because of this, I have started testing new deodorants to try and find a good replacement--this just doesn't cut it. The original (ANT and DEOD) product was the best "deodorant" product that I have ever found and I absolutely loved it :(

For the critics, I understand that this new version is intended to serve as a deodorant and antiperspirant because its fine print says something like "controls odor and wetness" but what I'm saying is that the formulation is different or something about the product has changed (other than the product packing/labeling).

column6: Andalou Naturals Fruit Stem Cell Revitalize Serum with Resveratrol Q10, 1.1 Ounce
column14: Had read review on Beautypedia giving it best rating in spite of fragrance noting it was very very little. Well it certainly doesn't smell very little as the fruity odor is overwhelming when you apply it. It finally starts to face an hour in and is mostly gone within two hours I find. I'm highly sensitive to fragrance so I bowed to never wear again after first application. However I was shocked and pleasantly surprised how it wore so well with my SPF and that I didn't mind the fragrance after it settled down not noticing it at all within three hours. So I kept wearing and I will defiantly repurchase. Lovely hydration without feeling sticky tacky or shiny. Soaks into skin within a few minutes and your skin retains that hydrated feel for the duration of wear. It's the only fragranced product I've ever worn that I haven't stopped and the only one I don't mind or that doesn't give me a headache or allergy symptoms. Can't attest to the multitude of anti aging claims it makes as I've only been using a month. But it pairs well with my prescription Tretinion tho I don't wear it with it. It just doesn't irritate my skin the morning after I use it. My skin does retain the plumped up look of the fine lines and deeper wrinkles as long as I wear it being in my mid 40's. The texture is thin serum like with the look of a lotion being yellow. It's not watery runny but it does slide down your hand when u pump it out so you must be fast applying from hand to skin. Pump works good too. No clogging even tho I'm low on the product now. Definitely will keep it in my rotation for anti aging.

column6: Hada Labo Rohto Hadalabo Gokujun Hyaluronic Lotion Moist, 5.7 fl. oz. (170ml)
column13: Big impact from an unassuming product
column14:
I really love this. Asian "lotions" are not what we think of as lotions/moisturizers: they're not creams, but more like hydrating toners with a typically watery consistency. This one has a very smooth texture that is just slightly thicker than water, and one drop is enough for my whole face, and another two for my neck and chest. Since it is hyaluronic acid, it may work best for you to spread and then pat it in (not rub! gentle patting is key) on damp skin, which also may cut down on the "sticky" feeling if that bothers you, although it goes away after a minute or so either way. I find if I feel like a need a little more moisture that day I prefer to apply it on dry skin, and if I need less, on damp just after cleansing. Give it a minute or two to fully soak in then apply the moisturizer of your choice: I find I only need tiny dots of mine now.

Honestly, at 28 my skin has not looked this clear or been this soft since I was a small child.

column6: John Frieda Sheer Blonde Go Blonder Controlled Lightening Spray, 3.5 Ounce
column14:
This product is great. It takes blonde hair and makes it a little blonder. Every time I get my hair cut, the stylist always looks at my hair and then asks me whether I color. When I tell them I use Blonder, they laugh and can't believe what a great job it does. I use it about every 3 weeks or so, just on my roots, and it keeps me with a very natural looking blonde.

The negative reviews on here are clearly from people who don't understand the purpose of this product. It's meant for blondes who want to be blonder. If it turns your hair orange, you aren't blonde. You may have been a blonde child, and you've been coloring you hair for so long that you don't realize you aren't a blonde anymore, but face reality. You are no longer a natural blonde. This will not turn blonde hair orange.

This product will work on some brunettes. Pretty much if your hair is naturally a cool tone brunette, it should work. But for anyone with warm tones, this will turn your hair orange, so stay away. It's really hit or miss for brunettes.

Lastly, the reviews of people who had their hair fall out all have one thing in common: they are mention how they are professionally coloring their hair AND using this product. Hair care 101 people: you shouldn't use more than one lightning product at a time unless you are a professional! And you should probably try test patches to make sure your multiple coloring methods don't do things like make your hair fall out!! If you are getting your hair lightened professionally, it's probably being bleached. And then if you use your own home bleaching product, I would be shocked if your hair didn't fall out!

I use this product about every 3 weeks, just on my roots and have being doing so for years. I have never had any damage whatsoever from this product.

column6: Pureology Perfect 4 Platinum Shampoo (8.5 oz) and Hair Condition (8.5 oz) DUO
column14:
I have been a loyal user of the Pureology brand of products for many many years (probably 15). My favorite has always been the Hydrate shampoo & conditioner (not the light one, the regular one, purple bottles). I tried the Perfect 4 Platinum on a whim because A) the set was nearly $10 less expensive than my usual Hydrate set and B) I had my hair high-lighted the first time in 2 years last week, it was lifted about 5 shades from my normal mousey-dirty blonde to really blonde platinum. This set is perfect! If you "bleach" your hair you know the "tangle" that comes along with the process. Sometimes even conditioning doesn't make it smooth, your hair just can feel just coarse while wet. It doesn't with the Perfect 4 Platinum system. I can comb through it easily after a just towel drying (my hair is a short graduated bob). After blow drying (on the lowest setting, of course) and then flat ironing a couple of stubborn strands, I can honestly say I'm impressed. My hair is smooth but not flat and shiny and not brassy. I like it and will definitely buy it again.
A couple of points of interest:
* The shampoo is a light aqua-teal blue, not the standard purple or lilac you would expect for a just for blondes shampoo.
* The conditioner does not have the trademark "tingle" that the Hydrate has and smells more floral than minty, it's quite pleasant.
* My hair is fine-to-normal, some natural wave, and cut in a short layered bob. I like to wash it every day and there's no build-up with Pureology.
* I only use a small amount of styling glaze and maybe a spritz of holding gel.
The set arrived on-time and was packaged in a padded envelope and enclosed in a ziplock bag. Best wishes! :)

column6: Evening Primrose Carrier Oil. A Base Oil for Aromatherapy, Essential Oil or Massage use.
column14:
started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the EO bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows. You don't have to pick up each oil and read the name. You can just glance from above. On top of that, they always offer free shipping!

In addition to all of above, PT almost allows one stop shopping for all of your essential oil needs. They have storage containers, carrying cases, roller bottles, natural body care, diffuser jewelry and carrier oils. I have very sensitive, reactive, allergic, rosacea skin. Have to be really careful of what I use on it. Several years ago, I gave up using chemicals to moisturize and only use oils. Evening Primrose is recommended for rosacea and wrinkles. Since I'm 63 and have rosacea, it's a good oil to add to my rotation. Right now, my skin is having problems with redness and bumps on the cheeks.. Pretty sure it's because allergy season is starting. I had started to make my own facial serums using carrier oil and EO skin synergies. I don't think it 's the time to experiment. Fall will be better. However, I started to add Evening Primrose to my rotation and so far it's been good. Time will tell the rest!

I received this product at a discount for an honest review.

column13: DISAPPOINTED IN FASHION FAIR OWNERS, BUT APPRECIATE AMAZON COMING TO THE RESCUE
column14: Fashion Fair products are perfect for me and many others.  The pressed, loose and cream-to   powder "shades" are amazing.  They have been able to match the "tones" in various skin types better than any other cosmetic company I know  -  and I have tried a great many.   Also,  their products have a very beneficial effect on the skin of both Blacks and Whites (I have white girlfriends who love Fashion Fair as well.)  Flaws in the skin are actually corrected as the products are used over time.  However, Fashion Fair should be ashamed of themselves for letting their customers down the way they have.  Almost all of their products have left the shelves of Macy's, Carson's and other Department Stores that have stocked Fashion Fair, WITHOUT EXPLANATION.  A few weeks ago I received a response to a letter I wrote to them in March, 2015.  It stated that they are still in business and that they are coming back with products.  They still did not say when.  Very Disappointing. I do really appreciate that someone had some of their products in my particular shade.  Thank you very much.  Suzanne M. Turner

column14:
First, taking the soap out of the non descript cardboard box was very interesting, you don't often expect to find black soap. The first thing I noticed was the aroma, it's hard to describe it's not bad at all just different.

Use, this is the very first soap I've ever used that when wet it's very slippery, yet as you run the soap over the body it seems to grab the skin at times. I'm not sure why it does this, I like to think it was grabbing the dirt and oils. Unlike our normal soap, this rinsed off very easily which I liked, and didn't leave a slick feeling that takes extra rinsing to get off.

Once I'd dried off I noticed that my nose and forehead where extremely clean and no oil what so ever.

This is what I mean by the first soap I've ever used, as a man in the early 40s, and disabled vet, I've used tons of different types of soap, and always had issues with oily skin. And this after only one use, wife's going to be mad because I'm now going to steal her soap lol.

column6: Photo Finish Professional Airbrush Cosmetic Makeup System Kit / Fair to Medium Shades
column13: This causes Zombie Face! Creases look MUCH worse.
column14:
It covered well, and felt light on my skin. A little didn't go a long way with me. I have naturally blushing cheeks, and wanted to cover that, as well as dark circles under my eyes. This will increase the look of any creases you have in your skin (wrinkles look deeper), so you can't really use it on your eyes. Once it's on your skin, you can't touch it in ANY way. No one else can, either. Forget it if you have an itch on your face, or get water or sweat anywhere. You will start to look like a zombie. And forget about touching it up, you can't. You basically have to take it all off and start from scratch.

The airbrush machine itself was pretty good, and easy to use, but it's just not worth the risk of wearing this stuff out of the house when so much can ruin it completely with no hope of touching it up.

If this review was helpful to you, please give it a thumbs up.

column6: Anti Aging Cream For Face - Best Moisturizing Cream and Wrinkle Treatment - Skin Cream for Dry Skin - Filled with Organic Antioxidants + CoQ10 + Hyaluronic Acid + Vitamins - 2oz
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Mild sharp herbal scent.
~ Feel during application: The heavy white cream spreads smoothly and feels moisturizing.
~ Feel after absorption: Moisturized, slight protective film that isnâ€™t unpleasant or heavy.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Oily skin types might find this too heavy for the face. Excellent for dry skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 2oz plastic wide-mouth jar with screw top.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Skin looks brighter and fresher.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Lots of beneficial ingredients in this including a ton of excellent herbal extracts. If youâ€™re looking for a moisturizer that also packs a healing and anti-aging punch, this would be a good choice. This has more and better active ingredients than many serums.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Folliform DHT Blocker for Men and Women | Natural Hair Regrowth Treatment
column13: USEFUL for BHP and FIGHTING PROSTATE CANCER
column14:
First off, if you are a bald man, sorry. You're bald. Go ask Trump where he got his toupee. If you are a balding man, in the early stages, this will help a little bit. If you are a balding woman, it will probably help even more. So what is the BEST use for FOLLIFORM? Actually, everything in this bottle is designed to help with BPH, or an enlarged prostate. Baldness, and enlarged prostates, are both caused by the same chemical process. Testosterone turns into DHT, which works on a man's body to increase his manliness, including baldness and a big prostate. Women have testosterone in their bodies as well, and it also can convert to DHT, which is one of the main reasons you'll see baldness in women. Genetics are obviously at play too, and nothing will change that. Lets look at the ingredients.
SAW PALMETTO -- these berries help to curb the production of DHT, and really help prostate problems.
NETTLE ROOT -- this is used to fight DHT production, and keep the urinary track clean. A nettle extract applied to scalp, can help curb baldness.
GREEN TEA -- a little stimulation, a little bit of phytochemicals, fights free radicals.
PUMPKIN SEED EXTRACT -- this is primarily used for urinary track problems in men.

Honestly, it looks like this preparation was designed to combat BPH in men, but it didn't market well, so they changed the label to say it fights baldness. Mostly it can, too, in some situations. I'm taking away a star, because of some of the things on the bottle, which are misleading. Is DHT harmful? No, its a natural component of men's biochemistry, and responsible for most of our secondary sex characteristics. In some situations, the DHT can cause BPH, which CAN BECOME harmful.(if it leads to prostate cancer.) Can this product regrow hair? Yes, but only in SOME situations. Hair loss isn't always caused by DHT, in which case, this wont help, nor will it help anyone who's hair is really gone. Can it increase hair thickness? Again, if you are talking about thick as the opposite of "thinning" hair, yes, in some cases it helps.
WHO WILL BENEFIT?
1. A large percentage of women JUST BEGINNING to have thinning hair. (if you know your mom had it.)
2. A smaller percentage of men, who are just beginning to have thinning hair. (It will slow down the process, and minimalize it.)
3. Men with enlarged prostates.
4. Men in danger of prostate cancer. (This product's main usefulness, as far as health benefits, is right here.)
Listen, herbal medicine is no joke. These herbs work, and yes, that includes hair loss. However, this DHT blocker is most useful for men who have BHT, or even bald, older men, who are worried about prostate cancer.

column6: Badger - Certified Organic Cuticle Care- Soothing Shea Butter
column13: UPDATED: I Tried to Like it......
column14: Of the three Badger balms I bought, this one is the one I didn't care for. To me, it felt very greasy and it didn't absorb into my hands/cuticles half as well as the Badger Hard Working Hands balm, which is pretty awesome. The smell of the Cuticle balm isn't necessarily bad - it's sort of got a citrus/lemon smell, which is nice, but it is definitely a bit on the strong side. I just wish it was as good as the hand balm, which does have a light wintergreen scent but it's very mild. Overall, I'd say this balm just wasn't what I was looking for for my cuticles.  UPDATE: Well, it's been almost a month since my first impression review of this cuticle balm and I needed to post an updated opinion. While the greasy nature of this balm is still there, I do find that it will absorb into my skin if I just wait a little bit. I have actually used this balm on my feet  for my toes and it has made my feet look awesome, so I started to use it on my hands again but only at night so that I don't get it on everything. It's actually an amazing balm when I manicure my nails every week - it makes the nails and cuticles soft and the moisture really stays in the skin. I bite my cuticles as well, so having used this more frequently since I got it I've noticed that the skin on my nails is a lot smoother and healthier looking. It may be a bit greasier than I'd have liked initially, but I think it was because I was comparing it to the hand balm....while that is an amazing balm as well, I think the cuticle care balm needs to have a bit more in there to soften up the cuticles, so since I use it more at night, I'd say I don't mind it being a little greasier than the other balms. So, I would definitely up my initial review of 2 stars to 4 stars. Sometimes you just have to wait it out and see how something will work. This time around I was fortunate to end up loving the product.

column6: Philips Sonicare HX8331/11 Airfloss Pro Rechargeable Electric Flosser
column13: Don't compare to a \Water Flosser\" and vice versa. Compare to interdental brushes and string floss."
column14:
I purchased this item to complement my Waterpik. I like them both and would suggest that reviewers who rate this poorly based on performance against a "Water Flosser" do not understand the product. Think "sand blaster" vs. "power washer". A waterpik is not a Flosser and never will be. It is an high-power oral irrigator that helps you clear food and bacteria from between teeth and inside deep gum pockets. The Philips Air Floss is for blasting away bacteria and calculus growing in interdental spaces. I have periodontal pockets as well as large interdental gaps, so up until now I had to use the Waterpik, brush, floss, then brush with Oral-B interdental brushes. That's brushing between each tooth, both sides, 2-3 times daily. It was exhausting.

The Air Floss seemed like a good alternative to the interdental brush, and it is. In a fraction of the time it took to interdental brush I can blast with the Air Floss. I've only used it twice and have come away with better results than my brushes! So if I'm so impressed why didn't I rate it 5 stars? I rated a 3 because it broke after just the second use and I'm not very happy with the inconvenience; however, I'm so tired of the interdental brushing that I'm willing to go through literally dozens of failed units to get a good one, whatever it takes. When I get one that lasts I'll bump to a 5.

I'm not concerned about the failures because: A.) It comes with a 2 year warranty that Philips extends another 6 months if you register, after which I'm fine having to pay for another one; B.) I'm sending the unit back to Amazon within the return window for a replacement as defective, so the warranty period begins again with the replacement; and, C.) It seems from the reviews like they either fail right away or they work just fine, so if can get one to work by the end of 2.5 years I'll be in a good position. It looks to me like all the reviewers complaining about customer support were given freebeta-units to review and are just upset that Philips stopped replacing after the 3rd time. That's kind-of the point of doing these types of tests, to see if you've got the product right.

For all we know Philips knows/knew about the quality problem and may have taken care of it. If so, these Amazon sellers are not on Philips list of authorized retailers and there may be no way for Philips to call these units back before they make it to consumers. It would be like if you or I bought 100 units to resell from Walgreens...how would Philips know you had them?

Regardless, I'm writing this review for people like me that have to use an interdental brush multiple times a day. As I mentioned, I also have periodontal pockets (some up to 5mm) that necessitate the Waterpik, so I can speak to the fact that really their only similarities are that you stick them both in your mouth and use them both for periodontal care. I wouldn't want someone to miss out on the benefits because other reviewers don't understand the difference.

column13: but they were all good, so I gave it a chance
column14:
Was scared since there are only 3 reviews, but they were all good, so I gave it a chance.
Wow! So pleased. Solution is "smooth". I don't know how else to word it. I've tried MANY other brands in my machine. The very first press of the button and I was in love with the coverage, texture, consistency and color (mind you its the guide color)
I spray before bed, then sleep with solution on. Normally I'm restless on a spray night. I can always feel the stickiness, and have to be conscious of where I place my hands (because I can transfer color onto palms). There is zero stickiness. It is dry, dry, dry!
Then when I awaken, I always have that "smell". That stink that goes along with every solution I've ever used. The armpits are in overdrive and smell like they ran a couple marathons. Horrible. Guess what? Yup. No stink with this one.

I haven't even rinsed it off yet, I was so excited to write a review. Can't testify to longevity or color after rinsing (which makes for an incomplete review, I know). But I can testify that so far, this is my absolute favorite solution!! (I'm fair skinned, blonde hair, blue eyed--but love a dark spray tan. I bought the 8.5% and it is plenty dark for me)

column6: pureSOL Konjac Sponge - Original - Body Sponge, 100% Natural Sponge, Eco-friendly - Gentle Exfoliating Sponge, Deep Cleansing, Good for Sensitive Skin
column13: I like it, but it's probably not going to make its way into my regular beauty routine.
column14:
I recently received the pureSol Konjac sponge, which is made from the root of a Japanese plant. It is supposed to deeply cleanse your skin and massage away impurities and toxins in your skin. This is supposed to leave your skin feeling clean and refreshed.

I think my biggest issue is that when the sponge is wet, it is fairly soft. I personally prefer the rougher texture of a loofah, because I feel like the rougher texture is exfoliating my skin. Maybe it's all in my head, but I don't see how something so soft can exfoliate.

Because it is so soft, I imagine that the sponge would be good for those with sensitive skin. If you're skin is irritated by a regular loofah, then this is probably the sponge that you want to get.

It came with a little "easy to hang" suction hook to hang the sponge in the shower. This was certainly a nice touch, but unfortunately, it didn't quite "stick" to my shower tile. I don't think it was any flaw in the suction cup - just my tile.

A huge plus for me is that the pureSOL Konjac sponge is eco-friendly. It is biodegradeable, vegan, and 100% cruelty free.

I did receive a sample for review purposes, but I believe that all reviews should provide honest feedback. All opinions expressed are 100% my own.

column13: Okay product, but NOT a good value for the money
column14:
This product is okay, but is nothing to write home about. It's a bit expensive for what you get. I've used Dr Bronner's soaps that I bought here on Amazon and am used to getting 32oz of soap for what I paid for 12oz of this product. I haven't found this product to be either better or worse than Bronner's -- just much more expensive. Both this soap and Dr Bronner's have a smell that is what I expected from this type of soap and it pleasant enough. I like the smell of tea tree oil and mint and of both this and Bronner's soap. Both plenty of suds and leave my skin feeling clean and fresh.

The bottle of this product is made of a harder than expected plastic that makes it difficult to squeeze out much soap. Perhaps that is intentional, but it was surprising to me that the bottle wasn't soft and squeezable.

I was surprised there are so many 5 star reviews and only a small number of 4 star ones and nothing lower. I attribute that to the fact that the manufacturer sends an email to purchasers asking them to contact them first before leaving anything other that a 5 star review. That strategy works it seems.

column6: The Baron Cologne for Men by LTL Fragrances
column14:
I LOVE, LOVE, LOVE IT! This is my FAVORITE cologne for men.

I found The Baron in the 1970s -- I was 20-something - and got my then boyfriend to wear it -- yes, I'm female -- and I didn't force him to wear it, but he liked it too, and then when all the other 'girls' gave him lots of compliments about it, he liked it even better.

The Baron was originally made by Charles Revson company and has not been available since Revson stopped making it -- until this version by LTL.

The original "The Baron" cologne was very different from the other men's cologne that were popular in the 1970s like Old Spice, English Leather or BRUT -- which actually made me ill and gave me a violent headache.

The Baron is understated and not too sweet or overwhelming. It has a clean scent.
Women love it and you'll get lots of compliments because it is so different from other men's fragrances.

I don't know if the new version made by LTL Fragrances is exactly the same as the original that was made by Charles Revson, but if it is anything close -- TRY IT !

column6: 3D Fiber Lash Mascara - Highest Quality for Sensitive Eyes - Jet Black Lengthening Volumizing 3D Mascara by CatZeyes Cosmetics
column14:
I have short, light colored lashes and have found this product to work very well for me. I see a lot of people who have issues with application or confusion about the fibers. Hopefully my review will help with that.
You will get 2 tubes, one is mascara and one is fibers. The fibers are dry and loose, the mascara is just like any typical mascara. I suggest applying this before doing all of your make up, if that's not an option I would then suggest getting a piece of tissue and laying it under your eye to catch loose fibers that fall during application.
Apply the mascara to both eyes and allow to dry. Then one eye at a time, apply mascara again and while it's still wet get your fibers. Slowly pull the wand out of the tube, tap the wand to get any loose fibers to fall off. Gently tap the fibers onto the tips of your lashes. Don't stroke them on like you do the mascara, if you do that, the fibers will fall into your eyes. Repeat if necessary, just put the mascara over the fibers you just applied and add more fibers. The more you do it, the more dramatic it will look. If you haven't done your makeup yet, you can wipe away any fibers that have fallen on your cheeks or under your eyes. If your makeup is done, use the tissue to catch those falling fibers because they are not easy to remove without messing up your makeup.
I suggest playing with the lashes and seeing what works best for you BEFORE you intend to wear it out so that you can get used to the application process.

I received a promotional discount to purchase, test and review this mascara.

column14: I have tried several of the adrenal "support" supplements of Amazon for about 1.5 years and felt nothing improved.  Cortisol levels have been tested and they were repeatedly very low and was debating on just giving up and resorting to an Rx for the problem. I actually seems to work.  I started with just one in the mornings but my problem was the "afternoon slump" so started a second pill in the afternoons.  I won't' stay I'm running marathons but this genuinely has improved my energy levels and I also think my mood.  I'm not falling asleep in the afternoons, or having to caffeine up to stay awake, which is a positive change.  I am trying to avoid having to take an Rx for my deleted adrenal glands and hope with some time that this supplement might be able to help heal the adrenals after decades of stress draining the life out of them.  I would definitely recommend these for people that tested having low adrenal (cortisol) levels or even people that just need a pick-me-up or energy boost.  It doesn't feel like you drank of cup of coffee - it is more gentle and less agitating - but you can feel it.  I think it took about a month before I actually noticed I was feeling better.  I just swallow the pill whole and can't comment on the whole versus chewing them debate.  Suppose there might be some merit in chewing them to help absorption.  I'm ordering my second bottle now.

It took having a squamous cell carcinoma lesion removed from my shin to really take the damaging effect on my skin my skin seriously. I can now enjoy being in the sun again. I never burn but I still get some color. This may seem a bit pricy but it is worth every penny...I now have my whole family and their kids using Blu Lizard products.
Don't wait as long as I did and start protecting your kids skin too.

column13: Arvazallia Argan Oil Cream leaves your hair soft and healthy
column14: Just started using this product - I have not used Arvazallia products in the past, but I was tempted by all the good reviews.  My hair is coarse, freezy and damaged by excessive color/highlights.  When you first dispense the product, it feels too thick and sticky -- which would normally pull my hair and hurt my scalp (I have sensitive scalp and lose much hair).  However, you can distribute the product easily, as it seems to "melt" - not sure if that is because of warming in your palm, or from contact with damp hair.  So it actually does not feel heavy or sticky to apply.  I let my hair dry naturally, and it becomes a little stiff, but with well defined curls.  Once the hair is dry, you can crunch it and run your fingers through your hair, which relaxes the stiffness and turns your hair into soft curls.  So far, I really like this product.  My hair feels soft, not freezy, and has nice curls.  It is too early to see if it will help remedy my damaged hair, but it definitely improves the look and feel of my hair.  I will try other products from Arvazallia.

column6: Aquis Microfiber Hair Towel, (19 x 39-Inches)
column13: All that its cracked up to be
column14: i have short curly hair. I'm also in my late sixties which means that having well-defined curls is challenging. So i'm always looking around for new products and new techniques that will address my particular hair characteristics. When i read that regular towel drying actually stripped hair of bounce and that a microfiber towel would be much gentler and even absorb more than terrycloth, i looked around on-line to see what was available. I picked this Aquis towel because of its size and because it is white. It's turned out to do all that it promises as I wrap it around my head without rubbing my hair and in five minutes my hair is drier than had i rubbed my hair, then wrapped it with a regular towel. Mind you, it's not the towel that defines curls on my hair (I then put a defining conditioner on after its microfiber dry) but it certainly leaves my hair in better shape than before i began using it. After i'm done with it, i also clean off water from my washbowl and shower taps so that everything is left dry and shining and i hang the towel up to dry till next time. Never having used another towel, i cannot say the price is worth it, but its simple looks and its dense and silky feel, gives me the sensation that it is.

column14: After my dentist visit today I decided I needed to write a review. I owe it to this toothbrush. One year ago at my 6 month cleaning appointment I got some pretty sad news. While I thought I had been taking good care of my teeth, my hygienist told me otherwise. I was completely thrown outa whack by her discovery of heavy plaque build up and an extreme case of gingivitis. I had been brushing twice a day with my manual toothbrush, and so I decided I would step my brushing game up. I got some new mouthwash and was a more diligent brusher for the next six months until my next cleaning. I waited anxiously for the good news that my teeth had improved. But no!! I still had a heavy build up! I take my oral health pretty seriously and finally asked my hygienist what I could do since I thought I was doing much better. She suggested a good electric toothbrush. So, after doing some research I settled on this model, not wanting to spend a fortune.  I am so glad I did! At today's cleaning I was told I had a significant improvement! Very light buildup and virtually no inflammation. She actually said she was impressed! Hooray for this brush. Easy to use and did exactly what a wanted. I don't think I'll ever go back to a manual brush!

column6: Maybelline New York Expert Wear Eyeshadow Singles, Earthly Taupe 170 S Matte, 0.09 Ounce
column14: This is the perfect nude eyeshadow for me.  It matches my skin tone flawlessly and gives me a natural look.  It's completely matte and because the color is so natural looking for me, it hides the discoloration on my eyelids.  I'm so afraid that Maybelline will eventually discontinue this color, that I've stocked up and have several as backups.  I'm a mature woman and no longer wear a lot of makeup, especially eye makeup.  But I use this shadow all over my lids with a matte white shade as a browbone highlight.  This gives me a wide awake look and with a ton of black mascara and defined brows, makes me look polished without aging me.  I sometimes pop a darker shade on the outer third of my lid if I'm going out at night, but this is rare.  For years I looked for a matte shadow just this color in high end brands and eventually started scoping out drugstore brands.  I found this quite by accident one day.  It looked a bit darker than I wanted, but it was on sale so I really had nothing to lose.  However, once I actually applied it to my lids, I was pleasantly surprised that the color was precisely the one I had been searching for for so long.  I'm light, but not fair, with dark blond hair and hazel eyes and this is the perfect nude, invisible shade for me.  I use it with a primer and that helps it last all day and this way, it hides the purple and red blotches on my lids.  This shadow is not highly pigmented so a primer is a must, at least for me.  And I love the matte finish (which I need at my age, lol!).  If you want a truly nude shadow and have a light to medium complexion, then this is the color for you.  And the best part is that it's really cheap, so if you like it stock up, you never know when Maybelline will decide to stop making it.  I definitely recommend this color.

column6: Hair Color & Conditioner- Burgundy Light Mountain 4 oz Powder
column13: I really enjoy Light Mountain's hair product
column14:
I really enjoy Light Mountain's hair product. The conditioning is amazing...it has truly repaired and restored my very, very damaged and abused hair. I was facing going short (my hair is just above my bra strap) to get rid of damage and tried this as a last-ditch effort to "save" my hair. It worked! It looks twice as thick, is stronger and feels amazingly silky.

I've used this color (Burgundy) as well as Bright Red, Light Brown and Red. Just a word of caution ~ some of the colors contain quite a lot of indigo along with the henna. This is not a bad thing all the way around, but my previously-bleached hair grabs the indigo more than the henna, which leaves me with a drab greenish/blackish/bluish hue until it starts to fade out in a couple weeks. That was the case for me with burgundy and with light brown. My fault though!

DO THE TEST STRAND like the manufacturer recommends because you really won't know how your hair will react (colorwise) until you do! TOTALLY MY FAULT as I chose to skip the strand test each time because I'm an inpatient risk-taker and when using this product, I'm after the conditioning/renewing/restoring effects more than the color! If you strand test and you do not like the results, Light Mountain will send you a coupon to try another color! So just do it! ;)

Also, follow the directions completely. I see so many reviews that criticize this product while at the same time describing some sort of "alternate" method or recipe using this product. If you don't follow their instructions, you cannot complain! ;)

As far as mixing and application goes, some colors require a cure time and some don't. The mixture is like a clay/mud and it does smell very herbaceous, which I LOVE. I use a lot of herbs and essential oils, so maybe someone less familiar with these "natural" scents would mind. The scent does tend to stick around for 3-5 days after using, even after I finally shampoo (I wait 48 hours before shampoo'ing, just using conditioner) and it does start to ever-so-slightly annoy me as the scent goes from lovely herbal to faded-herbal but it's not something to knock this product for, as it's just the nature and properties of henna, indigo and/or cassia (aka natural hair color).

One final note, since my hair had been bleached/dyed so many times prior to using Light Naturals that it does not come out very red on me at all right now, I decided to amp up the red color by using Manic Panic over it, between applications. (Note: It does take more red on my "virgin" hair but the ends/damaged parts don't stay reddish long. This is another normal thing with henna on very processed hair.) I've read warning that using henna frequently can make the hair too dark (and I don't want it darker) so I decided to try MP between Henna'ing and it works GREAT! Now I Henna every 8-12 weeks and do MP every 6 weeks or so. It's a great combination and my hair has never felt better.(I wait 48 hours before shampoo'ing, just using conditioner) and it does start to ever-so-slightly annoy me as the scent goes from lovely herbal to faded-herbal but it's not something to knock this product for, as it's just the nature and properties of henna, indigo and/or cassia (aka natural hair color).

column13: Only thing that's worked for me
column14: I unknowingly acquired a planter wart on the bottom of my foot after getting a pedicure at a salon. Unfortunately, since I did not notice it, it ended up spreading. Eventually I had five different warts in various areas of the soles of both of my feet. I tried pretty much anything that promised to remove them over the span of two years. I tried the duct tape which did help with two very small warts. I tried multiple over the counter products and none of those worked one bit. I tried apple cider vinegar which did help to make the plantar warts smaller but was taking a VERY long time. I finally found this and decided to try it. I start by taking a shower to soften up the skin on my feet, use a pumice stone only on the plantar wart to expose it, and then once the skin has dried I apply the acid using a q-tip just to the wart. I hold the q-tip on for a minute or so and then cover with a band aid. The area that I have applied the acid to then becomes calloused. Once the callous is gone, the wart is exposed again but smaller. I repeat this as frequently as needed until the wart is gone. I have removed three plantar warts this way. The acid did not hurt me when applying to the soles of my feet. Be sure to keep away from children and be very careful with this acid though as it definitely can damage your skin. Not something you want to get in or near your eyes. I always wash my hands well after handling.

column13: All I need to keep my feet soft!
column14: I am not a fan of the typical gray pumice stones. In my opinion, they don't work.  The Mr. Pumice stones are amazing!  I have used them for several years now. They are made of some type of synthetic material that actually scrapes away the dead skin and calluses on the bottom of your feet. These bars are very hard. I keep one in the shower, and about three times per week I put a little soap or shampoo on it, and scrub my heels.  It keeps the bottom of my feet soft without ever having to do anything else to them. As you scrub, sand-like pieces of the bar come off as it wears down. I think this is why they work so well compared to a typical pumice stone that doesn't "give" at all. After a while, the bar will wear down in the center, and I just flip it and begin using the other side. Eventually it gets very this in the center and needs to be replaced. However, each one lasts for months.

column6: clinique Dramatically Different Moisturizing Lotion With Pump 4.2oz
column14: I was appalled to learn of the change from the original DDM to a new product. It's the reason I started using clinique as a teenager, and has been the reason I have purchased most of my facial products from clinique ever since. Many of my friends feel the same way. This is THE product that keeps bringing people back and sets the company apart form all the others to choose from. Not any more. I tried the + version, and had a horrible experience with it. My face didn't absorb the moisture, and felt greasy and itchy all day. I kept trying it and it got worse. I then stocked up on all I could of the originals from outlet stores. My supply just ran out, and I have been at my wit's end to find a replacement. I even tried the new DD Cream, hoping and praying that it was based on the original formula. Nope. Within an hour after application, my face felt greasy and itchy again. For the life of me, I can't imagine why on earth clinique would disappoint its devoted fans by changing such a mainstay product. Even on the clinique website, the DDL only gets a 75% approval rating, means a quarter of the users are unhappy. It's the same on Amazon and other on-line sources. I now have to begin a huge search for a new moisturizer. Once I find one, that's where I'll be taking my future business for all of my cosmetic needs, as I don't have the time to run from one counter to another. This is just terribly disappointing, and I really wish the company would listen to its longstanding supporters and provide the original as an option.

column6: Small Plantar Fasciitis Night Splint
column14: I have suffered from PF for about 9 months. My doctor's advice was to do the stretches and take ibuprofen. It took so much ibuprofen to treat my pain that I developed stomach issues. I do the stretches and use ice and a tennis ball... all of the things that I have been told or have read would help. I was reluctant to buy this boot though. Maybe because I've spent hundreds of dollars on inserts and shoes or maybe because I didn't want to hurt my husband (this boot is stiff). I finally gave in and ordered one, although I have PF in both feet. I purchased the Bird & Cronin brand because of the price. I've now worn it 3 nights in a row on my right leg because that's the leg with the worst pain: the first night all night long, but the 2nd and 3rd only about 2/3 of the night. Is the boot comfortable? It's not 'uncomfortable' - just bulky. You can't walk in it, and so when my dog needed to go out in the wee hours, I took it off, and fell back asleep without putting it back on. It's been 3 nights. My pain is so much better in the right foot that I can now really see how bad my left foot hurts too. I will order another and wear them both. I hate that I resisted so long.

column6: Lipstick Queen Lipstick
column14:
Do you remember the childhood fable about the Emperor's new clothes? A crafty tailor didn't have the Emperor's new clothes made, so he told the Emperor his new, stylish outfit was invisible. All the courtiers were in on it or afraid to seem unworldly so they raved about the new suit of clothes. They created alot of hype in town and announced there would be a big event to show-off the new duds. The Emperor paraded around town in the buff. At first everyone was horrified the Emperor was strutting around nude, but they were too afraid to admit they couldn't see the value in the new, much-hyped suit of clothes.
When I received my Lipstick Queen "Hello Sailor" lipstick, I was so excited to try this navy-to-mauve shade the description promised! What fun--a navy product that would turn the exact shade of mauve perfect for each individual wearer's skin tone! I applied this creamy, moisturizing lipstick and saw nothing. I had first lined my lips with a neutral liner, so I decided to try again after I returned home later in the day. After removing all my makeup that evening, I applied the "Hello Sailor" again on a naked lip. Creamy. Smooth. Invisible.
So, either my coloring (fair complexion, dark hair, light eyes) doesn't work with this balm's chemistry, or Lipstick Queen has duped me! I'm returning this moisturizing but invisible lipstick.
(c) KMS 2015

column13: Works well but I prefer Simple Micellar Water.
column14: I really like this product.  It removes makeup and even mascara, with a few swipes on a cotton pad.  It takes me about 2 to 3 pads to completely remove my makeup, but by the last one, there's not a trace of it left on my face.  However, I did buy the Simple Micellar Water when I ran out of the Garnier and I have to admit, I like it better.  It's fragrance free and more suitable for my sensitive skin.  It also removes all traces of foundation and eye makeup and I think it works a bit better than Garnier.  Plus, it's less expensive and can be found in drugstores rather than online (I've never seen Garnier Cleansing Water in any store).  It works just as well, and I think better, than Garnier.  From now on, I'll be using Simple.  Sometimes you find a product in a drugstore that works as well as its more expensive counterparts.  And this is the case here.  I'm sticking with Simple, although I do recommend Garnier and have therefore given it five stars.  But if you want a readily available product that works like magic, check out Simple.  I prefer it over Garnier.

column6: Color Control Cushion Compact Broad Spectrum SPF 50
column14:
Amore Pacific, based in South Korea, lists "alcohol" as an ingredient in its Color Control Cushion Compact with SPF 50. Since there are good and bad alcohols, I resisted jumping to a negative conclusion especially because I agree with AP regarding the impressive visible benefits conferred by their treatment foundation that has many fans atwitter and aglow.

AP's response to my inquiry was delayed, which I considered either bad (corporate communications) netiquette or bad news. After four workdays, I received a reply thanking me for my "patience" as a response from R&D "to ensure correct information and advice" had not yet been received. When I informed the company that I HAVE no patience and am spoiled by live chats, which provide instant gratification, I received an answer two days later. Apparently, bamboo sap, the primary moisturizing ingredient, is easily contaminated as it's stored for prolonged periods. To prevent "micro-organic pollution," anhydrous alcohol is used. This is ethyl alcohol, which some scientists who write for respected journals warn consumers to avoid because it penetrates the skin barrier and provokes short- and long-term harm, exacerbates oily skin and redness, and may even minimize the efficacy of good ingredients including those that protect against sun damage.

AP is the parent company of Sulwhasoo, which makes a Perfecting Cushion that also includes "alcohol" but not bamboo sap. I don't know what ingredient(s) this brand is protecting.

AP asserts that their anhydrous alcohol is dermatologist approved, but we have no idea who the dermatologist is and whether or not the doctor was paid. AP says that their anhydrous alcohol is patented, but this is just ethyl alcohol with water removed and can't be patented.

The respected Washington, D.C.-based Environmental Working Group (EWG) rates this alcohol a 2 (out of 10) and asserts that anything between 1 and 2 is "low hazard." The overall EWG rating for AP's Color Control Cushion Compact is "4," meaning that it is of *moderate* concern to human health. (The nonprofit group objects most strenuously to the sunscreen octinoxate and to the fragrances included.)

Our U.S. FDA approves the use of ethyl alcohol.

In 2008, the National Institutes of Health urged further investigation, but rigorous double-blind, peer-reviewed studies demand a lot of time and money. Meanwhile, concern lingers.;low hazard." column14:
How do you compare hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Grapefruit, from natural essential oil
~ Feel during application: This is an orange (from antioxidants, not colorants) thick liquid that feels like a smooth, light lotion going on.
~ Feel after absorption: Unfortunately, sticky on my skin. This bothered me on my hands and arms. On my neck, where itâ€™s intended to be used, it was still sticky but I didnâ€™t really notice.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: On your neck, it should be fine for all types.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 1.7oz plastic container with broad plastic pump.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* There is a slight cosmetic tightening effect. I suspect this is where the sticky nature of the formula comes in handy.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Excellent. Packed full of anti-aging, skin-rejuvenating, moisturizing ingredients. This has all the hallmarks of a truly effective formula.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

LOVE THIS! I have had this steamer for three weeks and have used it twice a week. I have had acne prone skin all of my life and now that I'm in my late 30's, I also need to worry about wrinkles :( The steamer is the perfect size, it's small so I'm able to put it away without it taking up too much space. It's very simple to use, plug it in, add water to the compartment, turn it on and it steams for about 8-10 minutes. It does have a plastic scent to it, but it does go away with time and continued use. I've added tea tree oil only once and it worked fine.

Just in case you are not sure what to do, the following regimen has been wonderful for my skin. First I wash my face with my Clarisonic using a gentle, oil-free, soap-free cleanser. Then I steam and I immediately put on a mask (Peter Thomas Roth Sulfur Cooling Mask). I follow with a gentle toner (Thayer's Alcohol-Free Cucumber Witch Hazel), an acne clearing gel (Peter Thomas Roth AHA/BHA gel), and lastly a brightening serum (Peter Thomas Roth De-Spot--this stuff is AMAZING). I know it seems like a lot of products but I do this twice a week and my skin has been responding incredibly well. My breakouts heal much quicker and my skin has been so soft and clearer. I highly recommend!!

column14:

Some growth was seen with the shampoo I used but then I tried this and it's thickening fairly nice, the length is a slow process but still much faster than other products I've tried. Best of all is the strands are not frail when they regrow and thus this why I'm rating 5 stars. The smell isn't the best but the other products I use masked it well so I don't shed tears over it.

Again I always like to stress that I deep condition my hair once a month and keep shampooing to minimum, the routine you used in your hair will effect the rate of success of any product you use as will the texture of your hair so your time frame may or may not match mine.

It is better for use in the shower and you need some gel to get the best shave from it. Dry it works well on a light beard but isn't so good for a heavier one. If you try it, you may need to wash your hair with dish soap a few times to really get the hair clean.  (A vinegar rinse afterwards is great, too, if you use shea on hair.)

column6: Crest 3D White Professional Effects Whitestrips Dental Teeth Whitening Strips Kit, 20 Treatments - Lasts 12 Months & Beyond
column13: Space them out more for sensitive teeth
column14:
I wanted whiter teeth ahead of my wedding, so I asked my dentist for her recommendation. I've used crest white strips and dealt with painful sensitivity from them before, so I wasn't sure what to do.

Because my teeth are straight, she recommended I start with Crest White Strips before spending hundreds of dollars to have her whiten my teeth (I appreciate my honest dentist), especially since treatments in the dentists office cause the same level of pain--if not more pain she said! My dentist did give me VERY good directions though. First, she said to only pay attention to the "maximum" directions. So since the box says no more than 2 boxes a year, and 1x a day for 30 min, not to exceed those guidelines. But I should otherwise "play it by ear" based on sensitivity--the effects are the same even if the strips are spaced out more. Also, I should start whitening 8-9 months in advance of my wedding, with the 2nd round of strips 2-3 months ahead of the wedding to avoid sensitive teeth ... Read more

column6: Argan Oil Moisturizer and Free Beeswax Lip Balm-Lightweight Natural Face Cream-Moisturizes and Soothes-Use Daily on Dry, Normal, Oily and Sensitive Skin-Fragrance Free-Made in the USA
column14: I'll admit any product that has a free add on catches my attention.  The product has to be good, though, for me to continue using it and consider buying it again in the future.  I like the fact that main ingredient in the moisturizer is aloe vera juice.  I use aloe vera juice straight from the plant for burns and I have also used it to soothe an upset stomach.  All of the ingredients in the cream are natural: Morrocan argan oil, sweet almond oil, sunflower seed oil.  it's also cruelty free, paraben free, not tested on animals, and is vegan.  The cream is a little thicker than I had anticipated but it did absorb into the skin well.  I will add this product to my daily beauty ritual and will use it after washing my face.  I haven't tried using it as a foundation without applying a primer first, but it goes on good enough that I think it should be okay.  It is for all skin types so my daughter can use it as well.  The bonus lip balm is already in my purse.  I would have preferred it not have a vanilla scent because perfumes sometimes cause me to get migraines.  That was an added bonus with the moisturizer - no fragrance.  I received a discount on this product in exchange for writing an honest and unbiased opinion.  This works as well as moisturizers that cost a lot more and does what it promises.

column14: I am quite a fan of Remington hair dryers and while my old one is still quite functional, I prefer the newer Remington AC2015C T|Studio Silk AC Professional Hair Dryer.  The newer model has basically the exact same functions as my older, far more expensive model; 1875-watt motor, two attachments, the heat settings, three speeds, and a cold air setting.  The newer Remington AC2015C is heavier, which I actually prefer, the attachments are about 50% smaller, another bonus for me, as I already have straight, thin hair, and the other attachments were too much attachment for my needs.  This ceramic model has a coating that I like; it keeps my hands from slipping.  The control buttons are still on the underside of the handle, which I prefer, as it is easier to adjust, in my opinion.  This model appears to dry my hair faster than my older, more expensive model, and both offer a smooth, frizz free finish.  I would highly recommend this hair dryer, it does what it says it does and the price is fantastic.

column14:
Ignore the directions, mix with coffee, I add a few drops of clove oil or powdered clove - that makes it smell really nice - as opposed to smelling like dirt...let it sit for at least 2 hours, or overnight, and leave on hair for 2-3 hours. It will NEVER fade. I have to do my roots often because my hair grows fast, I'm about 30% gray on 70% brunette, so every 4 weeks I just apply to the roots, because, again, it DOES NOT FADE. I swim in highly chlorinated pool water 1-2xs a week for 30 min.s, no cap, no fade. I did quite a bit of research, this product is the s***, very pure and totally consistent. The color is gorgeous, it will vary according to your own color, for me it's new copper penny, super healthy and people think it's natural (I tell them it's henna because I'm a huge advocate of not putting poison into our scalps). Three of my friends are converts, you will be too ! I have applied it myself, it's not too bad, but usually I mix it up and bring it to my hairdresser to apply, go home with
a plastic cap and a doo rag - just like Lucy : ) kill a couple of hours, then rinse out it the shower with several hits of cream rinse (I like coconut). It goes right down the drain, a bit of a hose down of the shower, and Ta Da ~ it's beautiful ! Do It !!

Pain/Inflammation reduction
Deodorant
Helps bring down fevers
Helps heal wounds
and can help with kidney stones/infections.

column13: Truly effective active ingredients and formula
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!
~ Fragrance: Mild, hard to define natural scent, slightly cucumbery.
~ Feel during application: Like a thick lotion or cream.
~ Feel after absorption: Satiny moist.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be good for all. I have very oily skin that tolerates few heavier face creams, and this one actually makes my skin feel smooth and soft, not oily.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 2oz plastic pump-top bottle.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Skin looks bright, calm, and smooth. This is a great eye cream too.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Excellent. This impressive formula contains all the active and beneficial ingredients it needs to do the job it claims and then some.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

As a product tester I received this free or virtually so for evaluation and review. This does NOT mean this is a fake review. I was not paid for my review, or given any incentive or reward for a positive review. If you don't believe me, click my profile to see the poor reviews I've given bad products. My job is to give an honest opinion, not help the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column14: I received 50X Strength Hyaluronic  Acid Serum for Skin at a greatly reduced price thru First Botany Cosmeceutials, and Eagle Eye Review Group, and Amazon, for my unbiased opinions. This opinion is my opinion, and only my opinion. I ordered this serum because I'm now middle aged an I wanted something that I could use to camoflague my smile lines. Although they are barely noticable. I'm very subconscience about them on my face.. As I age I'm blessed not to have to deal with wrinkles, crows feet, or any other signs of aging. column14: I LOVE this toothbrush! Was hesitant on shelling out the money but glad I did. The vibration of the toothbrush gave my mouth a strange feeling at first that I wasn't used to, almost like a tickling but after a handful of times I got used to it. You know that feeling of slick clean teeth after leaving the dentists office? That's how my teeth feel every time I brush. The "polish" mode really leaves your teeth feeling slick so less food is able to build up. After 1wk of using 2x a day I noticed a dramatic difference in the tarter buildup of my teeth that regular brushing and flossing wouldn't take care of. The best thing about it is that I got my husband to use it as well and he loves it! It has helped with the overall appearance and I drink coffee ALOT and it has helped with whitening of my teeth. If you or your spouse are thinking about getting one, save some money and buy 1 and share!! It comes with two different sized toothbrush attachment heads. He uses one and I use the other. After I brush my teeth, I pop my brush head off and he attaches his on. It's like two for the price of one!! Ha. We will be ordering replacement heads in a couple of months, DEFinitely recommend!!

column13: The Fountain of Youth in a Bottle
column14: I'm writing this review after using this product for 6 months because:  (1) Sustained results over time are important to me; and (2) I'm a cynic and a skeptic who has no difficulty panning inferior products.  Let me tell you that I've never been more pleased with a Vitamin C serum!  I'll be turning 55 this year (arrrgghh!!) but thanks to this product my skin doesn't reflect my age -- or the fact that, as an adolescent and young adult, I was rarely careful about using sun block despite the fact that I have fair skin that burns rather than tans.  Daily use of this serum has not only corrected my hyperpigmented areas, but has also improved skin tightness over my face and neck.  After cleansing my skin, I apply this Vitamin C serum all over my face, neck, and décolleté -- it absorbs quickly and leaves no residue. When I used to have dark spots (which this product has corrected!), I applied another little bit over the hyperpigmented areas, then followed with moisturizer in the morning and then before bed.  I've also had great results using this product on my hands and forearms, to get rid of the nasty results of sun overexposure (LOL!).  Suffice to say I'll never be without this amazing Vitamin C serum -- it out-performs products that are 8X as expensive.  Do your skin a favor and try some -- you won't be disappointed!

column6: USpicy makeup brushes
column13: ... looking for something that would help me get more comfortable using a variety of brushes and also hone in ...
column14:
In purchasing these brushes I was looking for something that would help me get more comfortable using a variety of brushes and also hone in on what techniques I find most effective. While the face, powder, and blush brushes are absolutely divine, the eye shadow brushes aren't my cup of tea. They're very stiff, meaning it's difficult to blend shadows and powder eye shadows tend to flake at their touch, resulting in a lot of product fall out. The smaller lip and eye liner brushes are generally of a higher quality, except when it comes to the fine liner brush. I am incredibly disappointed in the shoddy construction of the bristles. They're cut incorrectly and applying any kind of liner with the brush is impossible. I'll probably end up having to trim and pluck the bristles myself. The makeup roll leaves much to be desired as the brushes are constantly falling out.

Over all, for the price, this isn't a terrible purchase. There are some winners in here and a good shampooing of the stiffer brushes may help the situation.

I would however, DEFINITELY recommend airing your brushes and roll out after receiving them. I scoffed at the people bemoaning the plastic-y smell, figuring it was your average, fresh-out-of-the-package kind of thing. I was wrong. Unrolling them the first time gave me a headache. I aired them out overnight and weeks later they STILL smell heavily of plastic. Be warned.

column6: CurlyGirls Combo Kit: All You Need Styling Essentials - Natural Hair Accessories for Curls, Coils, Kinks & Locs by Loccessories
column14:
I love my CurlyGirls Combo Kit for natural hair. I have 3a-3c natural African American hair similar to that of Mel B. When she wears her hair in it natural curly state. I did the big chop 18 months ago and have been learning the basics of keeping my hair healthy and manageable since then. It can be a long, difficult road at times, especially since I bleach and dye my hair.

For the longest time, my hair was short enough where all I did was wash it, rake my fingers through it, and walk out the door. Now that it's around 12" or shoulder length when straight, I'm having more challenges of keeping it from getting tangled, avoiding knots, and getting matted. I love the comb for parting my thick hair and the clips for securing sectioned pieces of hair. The spiral bobby pins are great at keeping my thick hair secured all day without the dreaded scalp irritation of normal bobby pins. The two large elastic bands are great for putting my hair up in a bun and they are so soft and gentle on my hair. I don't feel like it's ever too tight or putting unnecessary stress on my hair. I love the hair comb for placing at the nape of my neck to keep shorter pieces of hair from coming don out of my bun. I've yet to use the ponytail loop but I can see it coming it very handy.

Overall, I consider this a must have and a good basic strayer kit for someone new to natural hair like myself. It's so easy and much more affordable then trying to figure and buy a hair tool as you encounter a hair problem. Every basic necessity is here and nicely packaged. I received this product in exchange for a honest, unbiased review.

column6: Claror SkinCare Acne Treatment, 2.5% Benzoyl Peroxide Gel, 8 oz
column14:
This treatment is pretty good. I had been seeing a dermatologist for moderate acne with nodules and everything else along with it. The antibiotics and prescription lotions helped, but I reached the point where the nodules were gone but general acne remained. I didn't want to keep paying the huge prices for acne creams so I started looking for a non-prescription benzoyl peroxide lotion.

This is a good lotion. It does not prevent all breakouts but it stops most from starting, and most importantly, it makes those that start fade fast. It seems to bleach clothing it comes into contact with very easily, but it also treats my acne without overly drying my face. You should still use lotion, but you can use this product without making your face a dry, burny mess of flaky skin. Overall I would recommend.

column6: Philips Norelco Shaver 6800 (Model 1190X/46)
column13: It was a close shave, but I'm happy with my choice
column14:
When my old (15 years?) Norelco rotary told me it could use a break -- and who can blame it? -- I started the search for a suitable replacement. Consumer Reports had reviewed electric razors, and of course there were plenty of reviews on Amazon. I checked them all, and quickly narrowed my possible choices to Braun and Norelco.

Knowing how well my previous razor had held up while performing well, I knew I didn't have to buy the latest model. I did want a model that was no more than 12 - 18 months old, though, because real advancements are made. I tried to determine what those might be in several cases. My next step was to try to examine candidates in person, because the feel of a razor in your hand is as important as the feel of the razor on your face.

Braun and Norelco were still within a razor's edge of each other. The Braun had some slightly higher reviews, but my face was "used to" a rotary, and I liked the look and feel of the Norelco a little better.

What I didn't like, or didn't think I'd like, about the Norelco was that the trimming attachment that was been an integral part of my current razor was no longer a pop-up, it was a pop-off. In other words, I would have to physically remove the rotary heads and replace that part with the trimmer. That would make it almost impossible to trim-a-little shave-a-little, trim-a-little shave-a-little.

Ultimately I decided that this particular model (1190X), which was first released in 2014, met all the critical criteria, including price. If I couldn't deal with the trimmer attachment, I'd kick myself once or twice and then decide what to do.

As it turned out, exchanging the blades for the trimmer is a simple, easy to master, maneuver and far less of an issue than I thought it might be. Plus the trimmer has a comb attachment that makes it work in areas I where I wouldn't have used the exposed blade, which was the only option with my old razor. A fair trade, andit keeps the razor cleaner than the pop-up, which is something I hadn't thought of before.

And Norelco got all the emotional pieces right, too. The razor looks great, so I leave it on the counter all the time in its own convenient little charging stand. The lighting (charge indicators, etc.) is elegant, as is the feel. And the shave is terrific! Even though I had been using a rotary razor, it took my face about three days to get used to this system, but the shave was fast, comfortable and close from the first. It's even better now.

If you're looking for a rotary electric razor at a good price (I'm figuring that with amortization this one will cost me about $6 a year), good quality, from a company with a solid reputation, you've found it here.

column14:
These are really nice; took a few times before I got it to do what I needed but once I learned....gosh these are great!!!

I love being able to twist my hair in the morning and slipping a claw clip in and head out the door. That's all well and fine..BUT I also hate, hate, hate hair on my neck while I sleep. And anyone else who sleeps with a claw clip in their hair knows how incredibly uncomforatable that feels. Hence, my search for more recent inovations to the hair clip industry which led me to this item.

I need a little gel or spray in my hair to get this clip to work, but my hair is thinning due to medical problems (and that's on top of the thinness I've had since chemo). With a little gel, this clip is AWESOME!!! Slept with it in my hair last night and what a joy!!!

I was actually very surprised when I started slipping it in my twisted hair that my first thought was "there is no way this clip will take in all this "glob" of twisted hair but I pressed on. And let me tell you...it can take on a large amount of hair gathered in one place! And hold it - and hold it some more - and more - and even through sleep. Never thought it possible with this clip but it truly has won me over!

It is made of flexible plastic which allows it to be able to take in a large "glob" of hair with no problem. It holds without the clip pressure against your skull that you get from a claw clip. And it STAYS PUT where you put it all day and all night. Such a simple little hair accessory but really effective and easy to use. And like I said, even with thin hair with a little product in it, it works just as well.

I've never seen this in any store so when I came across it on Amazon I was intrigued. Read the wonderful reviews and took the plunge and placed my order and so glad I did!

column13: Very effective vitamin C serum formula
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!
~ Fragrance: Citrusy. No added/artificial fragrance.
~ Color and texture: This is a thick liquid the color of orange juice.
~ Feel during application: Smooth and slippery, feels somewhat like a moisturizer.
~ Feel after absorption: Moisturized and soft. No film or barely perceptible film.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: It works well on my oily, sensitive skin, and should be fine for others.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 1oz blue glass bottle with squeeze dropper top.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Lighter and smoother looking, with a reduction in very fine lines.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Excellent. Packed full of active ingredients for healing, improving skin elasticity, reducing inflammation, and fighting signs of aging.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.
