column13: Definitely did not prevent stretch marks but I still liked it
column14: I bought this oil in the first trimester of my pregnancy. It was my first pregnancy and a did have one or two very faded stretch marks on my breast from puberty. I used this and a few other products for preventing stretch marks during my pregnancy on a daily basis. I have since learned that getting stretch marks is more determined by genetics and how much your skin can stand to stretch. You can oil and lotion and grease yourself up as much as you want but if the stretch marks are coming, they won't be stopped. I did like the smell of this oil. Not too strong for me but a nice lemony scent. The oil goes on easily and absorbs nicely. The entire bottle lasted for maybe six months for me. I applied it to my breasts, belly, hips, and bottom. This oil definitely helped to lessen the itchy skin on the belly during pregnancy. It did not, however, prevent stretch marks. My breasts were covered in stretch marks early in pregnancy but I didn't get a single one on my belly until my ninth month. Then one day I woke up and my belly was covered in them. I will not tell anyone to not use anything like this during pregnancy. Just know that if you have skin that is genetically not built to stretch and bounce back, there are most likely stretch marks in your future.

column6: Revlon CrazyShine Nail Buffer
column13: So far it's the best I've owned!
column14:
So I can not wear nail polish on my nails. With my job my hands are constantly in water, so the polish doesn't last a day. Gel polish is also out of questions because I keep my nails very short for performing the facials and cut them at least once a week. So I'm trying to keep my natural nails looking as good as possible and naturally I went through a number of nail buffers. So far I think this one is the best. The main advantage is that it's only two steps. I've owned buffers that had as many as 4 sides!!! So obviously it took a whole lot of time. And by the time I had to do pinky on my right hand I was fed up with this process and did a sloppy job. Revlon crazy shine gives the result much faster. My nails were very shiny at the end. And the best part: even a few days later my nails still have a nice smooth sheen.
The only drawback is that of any nail buffer: with continuous use it will make your nails thinner.

column13: Replaces Lipstick, but at what cost?
column14: I order this same color (and several others) from Burt's Bees on a regular basis. They have now taken the place of my lipstick. I can't live without the nice cool, minty feel after application. But remember: If you use ANY type of chapstick, lipstick, ointment, etc. on your lips for more than a week, your lips become dependent on it. If you miss a day or two, your lips will become EXTREMELY chapped. Of course, putting your choice of product on again will help, because that's what caused it! Burt's Bees is no different in this regard. If you STOP using it, you get chapped. So it's kind of a which came first, the chicken or the egg? What caused the chapped, what stopped the chapped lips? Well, as I said, I can't live without the cool, minty feel, so I've made my choice. But it seems wrong somehow...

column6: Omega Nutrition Liquid Face and Body Soap Unscented, 946 Grams
column13: This is the basic dictionary definition of soap
column14:
This may just be the best soap possible. It is just plain soap, the basic compound, and nothing else. No scents, no enhancers, nothing but soap. You can use it as a base for whatever else you want in a soap, which is great. I agree with the reviewer who said it has a slight oatmeal scent. This is probably just what plain soap naturally smells like. Also, I agree with the reviewer who said it is very watery. It is, which can be problematic. This is not what people normally consider concentrate and probably could be concentrated even more. In any case, I have found that you can dilute it to about 1/3 or so and it is still an effective soap with a puff. And best of all, it works to the end, unlike a bar of soap, which seems to have static or magnetism that prevents it from lathering well near the end. Has anyone else noticed that?

I definitely recommend this because its the most basic soap possible, and thus the healthiest. I am sure some concoctions are better, but this is back to basics. I am, however, docking a star because calling it concentrated is misleading considering how watery it is.

column6: Thinksport Livestrong Sunscreen SPF 50+, Water Resistant, 3 ounces
column14: The ad referenced a protection factor of 50+ with Zinc Oxide 20% as the active ingredient. I concluded the product would significantly provide more shielding from UV rays than similar sunscreens with a lesser rating.  How wrong I concluded.  I sustained a first degree sunBURN on the applied areas of my arms, shoulders, and neck. Additionally, the product (ordered June 21) was delivered June 27 with the stamped expiration date of 9/15.  Brick-and-mortar stores selling lower-rated sunscreen factors have a longer shelf life than the rated products.  Two thoughts immediately came to mind.  The seller ships near outdated stock OR ships current stock manufactured with short expiration dates to promote ongoing purchases of an ineffective product.  Perhaps, the active ingredient oxidizes and become inert promptly after manufacturing. column13: Great kit to start your collection!
column14:
I started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the EO bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows. You don't have to pick up each oil and read the name. You can just glance from above. On top of that, they always offer free shipping!

While this is called the "Spring Cleaning Set," it contains great oils to start your EO collection. Lavender is the "universal" oil--it's calming, reduces stress, promotes sleep, helps skin issues, etc.. Tea tree would probably be the next most popular oil (maybe #3)--antifungal, helps skin issues, reduces symptoms of illness, etc. Lemon is right up there, too-- refreshing, energizing, uplifting and sanitizes. With the exception of Peppermint and Germ Fighter Synergy, the oils are child safe (Peppermint is not for children under 6, the Eucalyptus is not for children under 10.) Only other caution is to be careful with topical use of citrus oils, many are photosensitive and you need to be careful with your dilutions to avoid this.

The set comes in a nice gift box with a page of cleaning recipes. You can go on the PT website for other ideas for how to use the oils.

I received this set at a discount for an honest review.

column14:
I'm such a fan or Argan oils! I have been dying my hair since I was about 30 years old. So my hair has been dry and frizzy and not healthy looking for a long time now. I had just reserved myself to dry, brittle, frizzy hair. I have used other Argan Oil treatments and none have left my hair this soft. I put a small amount in my hands and worked it through my freshly washed hair. I use more than the suggested amount because I have long hair with a lot of frizz, and always need more. I mainly use it on the bottom half of my hair because that is where I have my main issue. I put a little more in my hand and then put my hair product on top of it in my hand (mousse) I put that all over my hair and it doesn't leave it weighed down especially at the crown. It leaves my hair very shiny and healthy looking. I'm very pleased with this oil. I have gotten several compliment on how shiny and healthy my hair looks now : )

column13: not for everyone, but works for my needs
column14:
Ok, it's not perfect. No, you don't get that perfect "I just shaved" as smoothness that makes you want to run your hands over your skin every time. But I have extremely sensitive skin, and no matter how many times I used a brand new blade, exfoliated, shaved with the grain, used sensitive skin shaving gel and deodorant, treated my post-shave skin with everything I was told to use, and whatever other advice I came across, I always had embarrassingly bad razor burn on my under arms. I would go as long as I thought I could get away with going before shaving, but it didn't really help. Until this nifty thing. So I read the reviews, decided to ignore the "legs only" suggestion, and what a difference it has made. Razors would irritate my underarm so much that it would sting to put on deoderant. I've only had this for a few weeks, so the irritation is still going down, but it has made such a change for me.

As others have said, try to pull the skin taut. If you have trouble with the pain, you can try kind of bouncing it, always being sure to keep it perpendicular to your skin, that way you're not getting too much pain in one area at a time. So, do a quick section, pick it up, do a section elsewhere, and so on. It may not be the most efficient method, but I was able to brave getting even around my bikini line in this way (obviously another sensitive area). For my legs, I still prefer the smooth feel of shaving, but I do get less irritation when I use this. Also, I'm much faster at shaving. So far, I've just been alternating and kind of doing whatever works out, which allows me to avoid shaving tricky areas like knees and ankles (where I typically tend to nick myself).

I should maybe also mention that I suffer from chronic migraines, so the pain was relatively very manageable in my case. Obviously it will vary between individuals.

In summary: If you have high pain tolerance and are willing to experiment a bit, this is worth adding to your arsenal of hair removal products, especially if you have sensitive skin.

column6: Sonic Face Cleanser and Massager Brush
column14:
I've had this for several months now and I'm amazed at how much different my skin looks now. This really cleanses your skin and prepares it for your skincare routine. Super gentle and doesn't cause any irritation. I usually use the side with the smaller bristles, but occassionally I will use the side with the larger bristles for a super deep cleanse. Since using the SOLO Mio, I haven't used any nose pore strips because this takes care my blackheads. As a facial massager, it's just OK. I tried it once and b/c each side has bristles, I preffered using it as a facial brush cleanser.

This charges in less than an hour and a single charge lasts for approximately 2 months. This only comes with the USB charger, so you'll need to either use your computer or a USB power plug.

This is obviously a generic version of the more expensive Foreo Luna and, though there are some differences, the Mio is just as effective. The silicone in both the Foreo and Mio are both smooth and non-irritating, but the Mio seems "thinner", The Mio does feel a lot better in my hand and costs a LOT less than the Foreo. The Mio advertises more speed, but unless you go to the extremes (really fast or really slow), the speed change increments are not that noticeable.

As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Smells like witch hazel, possibly in alcohol.
~ Feel during application: Like thick water. Itâ€™s a clear colorless thin gel. If youâ€™re looking for a non-lotion-based retinol product, this is a good one.
~ Feel after absorption: Vanishes into the skin nicely but does leave a barely perceptible non-sticky film. Application of a moisturizer or other product would do away with that.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: If there is alcohol in the witch hazel (and there may not be), it might not be great for sensitive or dry skin. But this is basically a very â€œvanishingâ€ product. My sensitive skin is mildly annoyed upon application.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 2oz blue glass bottle with plastic press pump.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Very slight lightening and mattifying.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Retinol, hyaluronic acid, and vitamin E are good for your skin long-term. Donâ€™t make this your only anti-aging product, but if you are looking to add retinol to your routine easily, this is a good choice. There are small amounts of some nice oils too.
*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Lavender Mist Facial Toner - 100% Natural - The Best Face Toner - Refreshing & Revitalizing - Nourishing & Restoring Ingredients - MSM, Aloe, Yucca, Spirulina, Gotu Kola & Vitamin C - Foxbrim 4OZ
column14:
This is a wonderful lavender mist facial toner. I like that it is 100% Natural & Alcohol Free.

The scent is light and refreshing. It doesn't linger long but provides a nice uplifting scent that is pleasant. I like to mist my face in the morning before applying my makeup and then at night after I was washed up for bed. It isn't greasy and completely absorbs within seconds.

The bottle has a nice pump top that delivers a good amount of product with just one plunge. A little bit is all you need and this bottle will last for a long time.

It is also good for a pick me up after lunch when the carb laden meal takes hold. Spritz your face a couple of times and relax while you feel the droplets sink in.

I think this would be a great addition to your daily facial care program.

column14: Update:I like the product for the way it works and looks and the light. After about 6 months it stopped working and I was disappointed. So, just before throwing it away I decided to take it apart and see what could go wrong. It s a simple assembly, easy to take a part and put it back together. It turns out the battery lead on a positive side was completely covered with white stuff (apparently battery leaked) and no contact was possible. I just cleaned it up and it works as new. On a flip side the way the switch is built it pretty flimsy, I would expect better construction, but probably must consider the price.  The product came next day as promised all intact. The batteries were not included. Once I put them in and used the trimmer, I really enjoyed the experience. It is comfortable, fits in the cavity pleasantly and cuts the hair effortlessly. The light helps to see inside for better trim. It easily cleaned and the looks great. I had 3 trimmer units before and this one is far better, i would completely recommend this item to anyone. The instructions however came intended for a different unit.

column13: This is excellent shaving soap for the money
column14: This is excellent shaving soap for the money, it is even more slick than any of my tallow based artisan soaps.  The soap is easy to lather and will accept a wide range of water contents.  Scent is subjective, I bought four of these soaps (Tobacco, Vetiver, Barbershop, and Fougere Noir) and the only scent that was not excellent to me was Barbershop.  Barbershop was not a bad scent it just smells to much like bar soap for my taste.  While on the subject of scent, do not judge the scents of these soaps while smelling them from the can, the scents really present themselves when you lather the soap.  The Vetiver is a sweet vetiver like Fine Fresh Vetiver Aftershave, The Tobacco has more cologne type tobacco notes, and the Fougere Noir is a great take on the Fougere scent.  It is hard for me to pick a winner between Tobacco and Fougere Noir.  If you are on the fence just buy this soap you will be treated to one of the slickest lathers in the wet shaving world.  As long a you do your part and control the water content this soap performs like a dream.

column6: [Tonymoly] New Egg Pore Set (Blackhead Steam Balm+Cooling Pack+Smooth Balm)
column13: Cosemtic use not a skin care by no means
column14: Ok, here is my two cents into Korean cosmetics. It is an absolute garage. This particular kit is (I guess) ok if you plan on using it as a cosmetics not skin care (by no accounts its a skin care) if you want to refresh the skin and maybe diminish big pores before maybe night out or smth. It is not going to do anything for your skin as far as making it better (as a treatment). I have learn over several tries that Korean cosmetics are based on "faking" the results, such as using whitening agents that used in sun care (not hydroquinone) to make your face "bright" and etc. It not a real result, my point is. If you really serious about your skin invest in BHA and AHA products (Paula's Choice are very strong and effective), invest in very good Israel line Holy Land Cosmetics. Basically if you want to use it as cosmetic line that is fine but it will do squat for your skin in short or long term. Trust me, I have had a life long skin issues and have tried everything from prescription to different brands of skin care. Tonymoly is more like throwing bandage on to bleeding wound, if you really want buy stuff that works for you skin. Do not waist your money on this one. If you just like cute stuff and have a great skin and want just kid around and use it just to make you feel better "that you are doing smth great for yourself" go right ahead. Its all depends on your goals, age and skin condition.

Normally my twist-outs and curl former sets come out very well and last at least 3-4 days with humidity and about 1-2 weeks in less humid drier weather. But when I used this product with my curl former set, (weather was about 70-75 very low humidity and mostly sunny) my curls looked great and shiny and bouncy that morning but by the end of the day they shrunk and was starting to revert to my curl pattern. I tried to pineapple my hair like normal to keep the curls longer but by the next morning the curls were flat sticky squiggles that seemed to be trying to revert while I slept on my satin pillow case. column6: Mistral Men's Soap
column14:
Pros: smells good; moisturizing; smells good; stays solid (doesn't get "shower soggy" like many soaps); smells good; sustainable fats; smells good
Cons: the scent is synthetic vs. natural; scent isn't as long lasting as I'd like (but still, smells good!); some ingredients have the potential to be irritating

I purchased this for my husband because I was tired of him using hand soap on places other than his hands: no, husband dear, all soap is not created equal. While this is not a "pure" soap (there are a lot of chemicals/ingredients that don't necessarily belong in there -- and I hesitated because the fragrance is not from essential oils), the majority of the soap is comprised of good stuff -- palm kernel and grape seed oils being the primary fats used.

The smell is positively delicious. There seems to be a heavier influence of the marine scent over the cedar scent, but the combination is positively amazing: clean, crisp, with woodsy undertones that make me want to bury my face in his neck and just breathe in. We're married so that's not too creepy, right? Beyond the scent, the soap itself has helped to soften his skin and reduce much of the dryness that plagues everyone who lives where we do. If I could only get him to use Man Moisturizer on a daily basis, the remaining dryness would go away.

column6: Dr Song 50% Lactic Acid Gel Peel (Professional)
column14: I got this when it first came out as an introductory price on Amazon, I believe it was 6.99 a bottle. So I bought two bottles many months ago and put them away and just never got around to using them. I decided to start using the serum because I'm starting to pay more attention to my hands and I'm making it a priority because your hands always tell your age, I see people that look fairly young but they have age spots on their hands and it just really looks unattractive and shows their age. I never understand why celebrities that are older but still look really good have age spots on their hands. Prior to this and I will continue to do this in conjunction with Dr. Song's, I've been using vitamin C serum and a vitamin C/retinol/tea tree oil serum that I got on Amazon as well and it has helped a lot including making a noticeable difference in the texture of my hands and getting rid of some dark spots from getting too much sun that  I had on my legs. If I didn't see it for myself I wouldn't have believed it but dark spots on my legs that I have never able to get rid of unless the dermatologist uses a laser and or liquid nitrogen which leaves white spots, this vitamin C concoction has eradicated my leg freckles and my hands look much younger. I want to really get the top layer of sun damaged skin off of my hands and keep this up so I don't develop any brown spots on my hands, also most importantly, I use Khiel's 50 SPF facial sunscreen on the top of my hands always, luckily I don't have any spots yet but I'm doing this as prevention. That being said I can't really say what the results are yet because I've only used it once however, this review is to let everyone know that I left it on the top of both my hands for five minutes, I did not burn at all, then I washed it off. I would've liked to of left it on longer but it was a test so the next time I'll go to 10 minutes + and see what happens but there was no burning, it was very tolerable. I want to try it on the upper lip where us ladies get those little lip wrinkles as well so  I will update my review later. The one negative with this serum is that it comes with absolutely no directions so I had to look on the Internet to see how people were using it because I would've had no idea how long to leave it on. column14:
This custard flakes soooo bad. I got it to use on my 4 year old daughter's hair the day before her birthday. I washed her hair, applied this custard while her hair was wet, and then braided the hair. Within an hour there were HUGE flakes in the hair and i was stuck. She was too tired and cranky for me to undo all the braids and wash her hair AGAIN and rebraid. She spent her birthday with huge flakes in her hair and I was not impressed.

The flakes: so to explain this further - this cream does not absorb into the hair and it does not evaporate. So whereever you have applied it it will just dry up into white flakes and stay there. Any of it that touches you scalp will form a flake and stay there.

I was so hopeful this would give my daughter's hair the shine it needed but it ended up doing way more harm than good.

column6: 4oz Premium Microdermabrasion Crystals - DIY Spa Micro Dermabrasion Skin Exfoliation - 120 Grit Pure White Aluminum Oxide
column13: Great starter for an at-home chemical peel
column14:
This is a must have product for anyone serious about exfoliation. Works great alone or you can mix it with any cleanser, because it's aluminum it doesn't dissolve so you can pre-mix if you so desire. My skin is very sensitive & every week to 10 days my routine is as follows.
I use the aluminum oxide mixed with Boscia Detoxifying black cleanser (it's a warming cleanser that really opens up your pores for a deep clean.) After rinsing & patting dry, I put on a thin layer of 30% Glycolic Acid & let it set for 3-5 minutes, I rinse off my face in cool water, using a cotton ball I swab on either a Ph neutralizer or just a mix of baking soda & water to neutralize any acid left on my skin & then do a cool water flush & pat dry. Afterwards I use Cetaphil lotion to keep my skin moist & if I'm going outside an amazing sunblock is a MUST. I choose StriVectin AR it's chocked full of retinol & NIA-144 for cellular repair. This is my routine & how I do an at home chemical peel for under $20 per peel.

column14: Beautiful powder box! column6: Emjoi Micro-Pedi Battery Operated Callus Remover
column14: I purchased the Emjoi Micro-Pedi a few years ago.  It came with two disposable rollers, a cleaning brush, and a plastic cover.  You will need two AA batteries for the Micro-Pedi.  This beauty tool is amazing.  My heels are often terrible looking and in need of some major help and the Micro-Pedi makes my heels look great.  I recommend buffing with your Micro-Pedi over a towel because it will be very messy.  There will be dry, dead skin flying from your feet like it is a blizzard if your heels are anything like mine.  You just buff using the Micro-Pedi until your heels are smooth and then rinse your heels, pat dry, and apply lotion.  If your heels are super bad like mine then it may take a few times using this to achieve the desired look.  When you are done pull the roller head release button down and the roller will come out easily.  Do not wash the roller, only the Micro-Pedi itself can be washed.  You must use the cleaning brush on the roller heads.  I am including some rather embarrassing photos of my heels.  There are two before photos, two after photos (only rinsed and dried), and then two 'after' after photos where I applied lotion.

column13: Didn't prevent stretch marks for me but still like the product
column14: I was given this belly butter as a gift in my third trimester of my pregnancy. It was my first pregnancy and a did have one or two very faded stretch marks on my breast from puberty. I used this and a few other products for preventing stretch marks during my pregnancy on a daily basis. I have since learned that getting stretch marks is more determined by genetics and how much your skin can stand to stretch. You can oil and lotion and grease yourself up as much as you want but if the stretch marks are coming, they won't be stopped. This belly butter has kind of a strong scent but I like the way it smells.  It is pretty thick and needs to be warmed up in your hands. Can leave your skin greasy feeling but it did not bother me. Really helped to relieve my super itchy pregnancy skin on my belly. The entire tub lasted for maybe two month for me. I applied it to my breasts, belly, hips, and bottom. It did not, however, prevent stretch marks. My breasts were covered in stretch marks early in pregnancy but I didn't get a single one on my belly until my ninth month. Then one day I woke up and my belly was covered in them. I will not tell anyone to not use anything like this during pregnancy. Just know that if you have skin that is genetically not built to stretch and bounce back, there are most likely stretch marks in your future.

column6: Merkur VISION Adjustable Double Edge Safety Razor- With Metal Box-#2000-
column13: A Noble Attempt but a Business Failure...
column14:
It was discontinued a couple of years ago, but a few NOS pieces are still kicking around. In retrospect, it was a noble attempt but a business failure. This is my interpretation:
In his typically excellent demo, Geofatboy called it the most "futuristic" DE on the market. He was talking about its looks -- I suppose it is right -- but its *nature* makes it easily the most "retro" DE I know of. That's what's relevant to the business failure.
It is a relic of an earlier age: A relic of a time prior to the disposable era in which it was normal that the owner do some routine maintenance and minor repair to keep stuff in good working order. In the disposable/instant gratification era, this isn't even tolerated. How else can you explain the prosperity of the disposable razor? In a culture that rewards that POS, the Vision had no chance.
As you surmise from the comments, shaving cream/soap residue left on the Vision gradually corrodes the delicate butterfly mechanism. It makes failure almost inevitable **unless the Vision is properly maintained**. In the disposable culture, that ain't gonna happen unless the owner appreciates its retro nature. Unfortunately, Merkur did a piss-poor job explaining that. It's only in a supplimental insert that they say "...it is mandatory to clean the movable parts with EVERY blade exchange thoroughly..." (Their caps!) Too few owners that got that message. I don't blame them.
It only will work for you if you enjoy little mechanical devices like this and would be happy to do perform the ritual -- as if the disposable era did not exist. If you're interested, it will reward you with the best DE shave I've ever had. It isn't that bad. Really!! You make the call:

* After removing the old blade, press down on that center T-bar while bringing up the flaps. This presses center pin down, letting you easily remove the bottom cap.
* Slide the bottom cap off and unscrew the butterfly knob (clockwise!). This frees the whole butterfly mechanism.
* Slide the butterfly mechanism out of the razor casing. That's it!

I follow Geofatboy's procedure for cleaning. To reassemble:

* Slide the butterfly mechanism back into the razor.
* Lock each flap onto its pin and bring the flaps up.
* While pressing the closed flaps down, screw the butterfly knob back into place (counter-clockwise!)
* Slide the bottom cap back onto the center pin and let go of the flaps.
The razor will snap into place. That was it. Enjoy your life.

It that's a big turn off, then look at the Futur in the Merkur line for something similar but w/o the maintenance requirements. And remember that Mr. Straight Edge is waiting in the wings -- but with even heavier maintenance requirements! Now we're talking serious RETRO!!

column6: Basil (linalool CT) Essential Oil 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade.
column14:
I started using Essential Oils regularly about 8 months ago to help with cronic allergies and to see if it would help with some other things. I really began loving them and make a lot of my own "stuff" with them now, including bug spray and cough mist...

I use most of my Essential Oils in a diffuser rather than orally and on the skin, and basil Essential Oil is one that I definitely use in the diffuser rather than orally.

I almost exclusively use Basil oil as a mosquito and bug repellant in the summer, but in the winter I use Basil for coughs and breathing issues. Mixed with Lemongrass and Geranium it seems to work just great keeping the bugs off! I made the mix and used it today outside as we ate, and with the rain we have had recently, and our water barrels, we tend to get mosquitos often. We didn't have any bothering us today.

The smell of the oil is the same as my other brands, and it seems to be the same consistency. While I did get a discount because of the change in the label, I would buy this again in a heartbeat at the regular prices. I think I want to try the cinnimonbark next!

column6: Glitz by Mottos Temporary Metallic Jewelry Tattoos
column14:
After seeing these tattoos pop up every where, I was really excited to get these in the mail. The tattoos on the sheet are well spaced out so it's easy to cut out the ones you want without ruining other ones. The instructions are easy to follow - clean and dry skin, place the tattoo where you need it, and then wet the back. I used a wet washcloth and sat it on the back. I was able to get the tattoo on with no awkward sticking to the paper.

They look utterly gorgeous on the skin, I've received several compliments on them. They seem to last for about 3 solid days and then after that the quality is give or take. I will note that the spot is really important -- one that I placed on my wrist wore out really fast, presumably because I move it ALL the time, whereas one on my upper arm lasted much longer. It is easy to remove these by scrubbing with a washcloth and soap, but just running soap over them doesn't seem to affect it. It's very easy to remove these with alcohol.

I do have two things worth noting. The first is that one of the tattoos was not flipped. It had the word "dream" on it, but when I applied it, it was then backwards on my skin and unreadable. Also, some of the tattoos were smudged. HOWEVER, I contacted the seller with these issues and they were fast to take care of the problem to make sure that I was a happy customer. Because of this, I definitely recommend this brand and will buy again. I did receive this product at a discounted price in exchange for an honest review.

column6: ASDM Beverly Hills 70% Glycolic Acid Medical Strength, 1oz
column14:
I was so anxious to use this product when it arrived. I usually use skin lab products but wanted something stronger.. Out of the blue in June this year my face started breaking out horribly in the chin and cheek area. I've been using different peels for over a year now however not as frequently, maybe once a month. Well after the breakouts i started to resume the glyco/lac 60, BHA, with no results. I then went to my primary doctor who prescribed doxycycline but I felt horrible when taking it.. She then switched me to aldactone but too low of a dose from what I have read.. After reading reviews i decided to try the Glycolic acid first before the TCA.
So I did the mild cleanse followed by the alcohol to clean the residual dirt, allowed to dry. I then applied the Glycolic acid with brush all over my face concentrating on the areas of hyperpigmentation and acne. Immediately started feeling burning sensation however it was tolerable.. Waited approximately 1.5 min after application before rinsing off with cold water profusely .. I never have used baking soda mixture to neutralize. After rinsing there is still some burning and frosting.. Applied bio oil all over face. Definitely some redness to my cheek area. I can tell there will be peeling in those spots.. I will update the review in days to come.. This was used at full strength.. I do believe I have a high tolerance to peels.. I will attempt again next week.. I do this in conjunction with salicylic acid peel

column6: Crest 3D White Professional Effects Whitestrips Dental Teeth Whitening Strips Kit
column13: Not a Review, But a Few Tips...
column14:
A Few Tips:
1) Place strips on teeth a bit loosely, (but not too loosely) then, using your fingernails, or the blunt end of a pair of tweezers, press the tape into the spaces between your teeth. This is where stains love to hide, and this is a hard-to-reach area that is difficult to treat unless you actually fit the tape in-between these crevices. The strips should now fit tightly and snugly. (Of course, do this before folding the strips over and behind your back teeth.
2) Use a good coat of lip-balm or Chapstick on your lips as this product can irritate your lips and even cause mouth sores at the corners of your mouth; a coat of lip-balm can prevent this.
3) Avoid using whitening mouthwash or abrasive toothpaste during treatment, as this will aggravate sensitivity. I suggest using a mild whitening toothpaste, like "Sensodyne Whitening" toothpaste) You may want to avoid very cold foods and drinks during the treatment time as well, such as ice-water, as this may increase your sensiti... column14: Best organic argan oil I've found, and the best value.  I have used this every day -- lots of it -- as basic moisturizer, several times daily throughout the day, on face, neck and body. column6: Merkur HD Slant Safety Razor 37C
column13: This is what you're looking for!
column14:
I'm blown away by how fantastic the slant aspect is. I have the Edwin Jagger razor and dropped it, breaking the head off. I did a ton or research and landed on the 37C being my next choice. This thing is incredible. The finish is nowhere near as polished as the EJ, but every other aspect is better. The feel on my face (I'm using Astra blades) is incredible, very smooth and quick across the beard. The sound feedback is great and I can really tell when I'm down to just skin. Nice weight in the hand and the ribbing on handle makes it easy to hold, even if some shaving cream runs down it.

If you're just about to buy your first safety razor, buy this and you'll be happy. If you're new to the sport, get a sample pack of blades to see what your face will take. Enjoy!

column6: No Tox Life Charcoal DETOX Face Wash Bar (80% Mango Butter) for Normal Skin, Pore-Purifying Activated Charcoal, Handmade Cold Process, 100% Vegan, Sensitive Skin (2.5-oz Bar)
column14:
*Note: My husband and I share this account - so this is my review, not his! :)

I LOVED using the DETOX face wash bar. I've used other "black soap" in the past, but they always tended to try out my skin. So while they worked nicely for a short time, after a week or so my skin would feel like sand paper.

I didn't experience that at all with the DETOX bar, in fact, it was the opposite! The longer I was using it, the more supple and soft my skin was becoming. It gave me a really deep clean, without feeling abrasive or drying. My skin had a nice healthy glow to it, and a more even skin tone.

It really makes me happy that it's hand made with ingredients I can not only pronounce, but I actually know what they are!! In a world of every kind of chemical skin product, it's really a score to find a natural product you can rely on.

I'm looking forward to trying more of their products - my husband and I are already hooked on the natural deodorant!! Definitely recommend that.

-Chelsea

column6: Essential oil by Morning Pep Happy with Your purchase or Your.
column14:
Of all the essential oils on the market, I consider Peppermint to be the most essential of the bunch.

Peppermint is useful for many aliments but the most common are:

Tension
Nausea
Depression
Headaches
Sinuses
and overall stress reduction.

I personally know that it helps with all of the above and seems to just help mellow me out in general.

I have a few oils from Morning Pep and I think they are a high quality supplier of essential oils. The quality to price ratio is really fantastic as well which is a great bonus. 4oz is a lot so even with daily use this bottle should still last you a few months so its a great investment.

I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for testing it out and giving an honest review. Having said that, the price is very good and I will most definitely purchase it in the future at full price. 100% worth it.

column6: Salicylic Acid 20% Gel Peel - Enhanced with Tea Tree Oil & Green Tea Extract
column13: Each time it actually made my skin better. It's like it is erasing bad layers
column14:
Ok, so facial skin is a sensitive tissue, I mean issue. I've tried this product twice so far. Each time it actually made my skin better. It's like it is erasing bad layers.
Which in essence what this solution does - it dissolves upper layers for you.
I follow up with Argan oil and it feels like baby skin. Hold your puns.
Couple of pointers: first time I tried it - I left it on for 3 min. Even though instructions and some reviews say to do less time. While it did some effect, I was left wanting more. I had to wait while my skin recovered of course and just recently tried again.
This time I left the solution on my face for close to 8 minutes and kept adding more on my skin throughout. Then of course cold shower on my face was imperative.
My point is that you will find your sweet spot.
I do get compliments on my skin now that it's unobstructed.

Product Description:
Beautifully Radiants Anti-oxidant cream will be sure to enhance the appearance, texture, complexion, and elasticity of your skin. Along with some of our key ingredients (Matrixyl 3000, Tripeptide 5, and sea fennel wax a.k.a Retinol), this top rated treatment combines all that nature has to offer. These plant based ingredients include aloe, sunflower oil, botanical hyaluronic acid, witch hazel, palm oil, coconut oil, cocoa butter, vitamin C, cucumber, beeswax, jojoba oil, tamanu oil, green tea, bearberry extract, blueberry extract, cranberry, raspberry seed oil, Oregon grape, licorice, camellia oil, avocado oil, geranium essential oil, bonage oil, flaxseed oil, evening primrose, rose hip oil, helichrysum essential oil, coenzyme Q10, vitamin E, eyebright, apple, lemon, sugar cane, lemongrass, vitamin B5, arnica, lavender, chamomile, grapeseed oil, and macadamia oil.

Although we labeled this little miracle an "eye cream", it can also be applied to any other part of the face. Whether it is your eyes, cheeks, forehead, or even your neck, you will see and feel the difference when you apply it. Feel free to use this to reduce signs of aging on your hands!
This effective product is great to use daily, morning or night, and for all skin types and all ages! Whether you have dry, normal, oily, combination skin or you are young, middle- aged or elderly, this effective treatment is a must! Beautifully Radiant backs their products with a 100% customer satisfaction guarantee! That means if you are not fully satisfied with our products after 30 days, we will refund your money NO QUESTIONS ASKED!
How many times have you spent WAY too much money on beauty products that guarantee that "Fountain of Youth" only to be disappointed by the results? Well, Beautifully Radiant is a woman owned and operated company who really understands. We truly care about helping women (like you!) recapture that youthful essence, without spending your life savings. That is why we came up with Beautifully Radiant's Anti-Oxidant Eye Cream! It is the ultimate solution to hydrate, sooth, and firm those under eye bags. It will make your skin appear healthy, youthful, and more plump.
Key Ingredients: MATRIXYL 3000- Rejuvenates skin cells by reactivating the production of collagen in those cells, gives brilliant tone, provides excellent filling of wrinkles, manufactures elastin. TRIPEPTIDE-5- deep skin penetrating peptide, stimulates collagen synthesis in skin, prevents breakdown of collagen, moisturizing. RETINOL- antioxidant, interrupts the free-radical damage process, effective in managing acne and eczema, corrects skin discolorations, reverses wrinkles from the sun, improves pore function and shrinks enlarged pores due to clogging or sun damage.
Along with our advanced and scientific ingredients, most of our formula is natural (70% organic)! We combine ingredients such as Witch Hazel (Hamamelis Virginiana) to help tone and tighten, and Vitamin C (Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate) to help reduce age spots, increase collagen production, and helps improve your skins defense against UV exposure! We have also implemented green tea into our mixture. This stops the signs of premature aging - like loose skin, wrinkles, age spots and fine lines - while making the complexion more moist and supple. Green tea also contains caffeine. Not only does caffeine calm inflamed blood vessels that create dark circles, it also soothes puffiness and tightens the skin, making it appear younger. These are only a few of many wonderful ingredients and benefits of this product.

This is an antioxidant eye cream. Matrixyl 3000 + Tripeptide-5 + retinol. This helps your skin by increases collagen production, minimizes wrinkles and reduces age spots. The cream is light and airy and has a light herbally scent, It feels so light and natural. With all the great

column6: NeedCrystals Microdermabrasion Crystals
column14: Before paying 75$ for a popular brand of microdermabrasion scrub, I decided to take a chance on these crystals and make my own scrub.  To be honest, I didn't expect much because because #1, they were so cheap, and #2, the label design looks like it's from the 70s. But, I decided to go for it and I'm glad I did. I love these crystals! They are like a very fine, white sand and I was surprised at how much comes in the container.  It comes with a tiny spatula for scooping a small amount of crystals. In a small travel-size container, I mixed a good amount of these crystals with my favorite face-wash and I LOVE how it feels when I scrub my face with it. It instantly smooths my skin. I've been using them for several months, and when I use them consistently, I notice a difference in the texture of my skin as well as how well my other skincare products work. The crystals slough off the top layer of dead skin cells so my skin is able to absorb more of the product. I'm excited to try some other recipes, such as adding a bit of argan oil or coconut oil.

column6: Iman Cosmetics BB Creme Earth Deep
column13: Great Moisturizer, Evener, Coverage for Some Skin Types
column14:
This is great for women who have normal or dry skin, like my mother, for whom I purchased Iman's BB Creme as a gift. Iman's BB Creme moisturizes, evens skin tone, and gives good coverage - blending so well that it looks as if you're not wearing makeup at all, and just have a naturally lovely, glowing complexion. My mother is in love with Iman's BB Creme and now this is all she will use. It's all she needs. What she is not in love with is the high cost of the product.

I don't use Iman's BB Creme myself because I am being frugal right now for the sake of my, and my husband's, goals for our family's future. I have oily skin, especially on my nose and cheeks, so I'd only use bb creams in the winter when my face tends to get dry. column6: Essential oil by Morning Pep Happy with Your purchase or Your.
column14:
This is either diluted with carrier oil, or very poor quality. I base this evaluation on two factors:

1. I have many bottles of peppermint oil from highly respected companies like Mountain Rose Herbs, so I'm very familiar with what it smells like, even different strains. This doesn't have even a fraction of the overwhelming strength of peppermint oil. It smells weak and "off." It does the peppermint tingle when I put some on my lip, so I'm guessing real but diluted.
2. Essential oils are highly volatile compounds. If you put a drop on an index card, it will before long have evaporated without a trace. No oily splotch will be left behind. This leaves a big oil splotch and also remains oily on my skin, a common indication of dilution with carrier oil.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column13: Leaves hair and body smelling fresh and clean.
column14: I ordered the Clean essential collection a while ago. I have been using it for over a week now. I especially love the dry shampoo because I am a busy mom I don't always have time to shower. Sometimes I go a day or couple days without a shower and my hair will get greasy and it will just feel unclean. What I love about the dry shampoo is you put it in unwashed hair and it takes the oil out and it gives the appearance of hair being clean, fresh and smelling good. The dry shampoo is not in liquid, gel or spray form. Instead it is almost the consistency of baby powder. It has a soft fragrance to it and smells clean. The set also comes with shower gel, body lotion, and body veil. The body veil is what I use after I get out of the shower it's good at absorbing moisture and leaving the body smelling fresh. So in total this is a four piece set, the bottles are not very big their about 1/4 of the size of an average shampoo bottle. I love the smell of this though. They use a technology that blends cotton seeds cotton extracts and cotton proteins to make a liquid or a dry form to create these bath products. So the overall scent you get from this is fresh clean and natural. All of these products are virtually scent free they're not going to irritate skin they're just going to leave you smelling clean and fresh. I really enjoy using the clean collection and I will continue to use it. I received this product in exchange for an honest review these are my thoughts and opinions on the project.

column14:
I have been using what proclaimed itself to be argan oil for years. Argan styling products, frizz products, etc. I have very thick, very curly prone to frizz hair that behaves as well as I do. So, I spend a lot of money on hair care. This morning, I used a few drops (ok, maybe 10, but far, far less than I normally use) and my dry ends soaked it all up. And they felt amazing. My hair felt soft, the frizz was gone. I styled my hair with this and I used significantly less than the other stuff and my hair was smooth, curls defined, soft to touch. I ended up just throwing some mouse on top for hold. I was amazed. And, a little mad that the 4 Argan products I use daily -DAILY - in my hair can't make it look half as nice. Really?

I also tried it on my face last night. It only took a couple drops, and it felt so smooth, not oily. It still feels smooth today.

The bottle came with with it's own dropper. It also doesn't have a smell. It really did take me forever to get used to the smell of the Argan products at the beauty store, but, I thought that's how the oil smelled. Well, I am happy that this bottle, at least, doesn't have that smell.

I was pretty happy for the chance to try this product. I received this product at a discount in an exchange for an honest review.

column14:
I used this product years ago when it had the Hydroquinone ingredient in it so it may not be helpful now since that product was taken off the market. I wanted to reduce the brown melasma spots, freckles and sun damage I had on my face. My dermatologist recommended this product and at that time it was about $350 for the pack. I used the product as directed and I did see results. It worked by sloughing off the damaged skin to allow new skin to surface. It was very strong but I did see results in my dark areas fading. The problem I had with it was that it worked so well I would sometimes get a flaky shedding of some of the top layers of skin when I smiled or at the end of the day. I lived in hot and humid Florida when I used it. I was in the sun a lot from just being outdoors. It's hard to avoid there even if you wear sunscreen all the time.
I recall being out with a friend at a bar one night and she told me to go to the bathroom because my face was peeling so bad. It was very embarrassing and I had some of the lotion/moisturizer with me so I fixed it after I had to brush off the flaky dead skin. Sounds gross but I want to give you an idea of what it will do. I would recommend this product and would purchase it again if it wasn't almost a thousand dollars!

It does not look dyed and a million times quicker and easier than gradual darkeners like Grecian formula which I initially tried fearing the horrible grey roots look with dyed hair. column14: Taking care of your skin is sadly one of those things that most people forget about until everything starts sagging and showing lines and wrinkles. With just a few uses, coworkers were noticing a difference in my skin and how it looked  - well, they didn't shout "YOUR SKIN LOOKS GREAT!" but they did ask if I had done something different because I looked "different" or younger and that it looked "dewier" (that one came from my manager who said that was a good thing, but I'm still not 100% what she meant by it!). column13: Good product, but didn't moisturize enough for me
column14:
I am over 40 with oily, acne prone skin and a fair amount of sun damage. Though my skin is oily, the area around my eyes tends to be dry. I wear contacts daily. My concerns are sun damage and crows feet. I bought the product about 3-1/2 months ago and have been using it daily.

I wanted to love this product, but have only liked it. The customer service was very good. I have absolutely no concerns about the quality of the ingredients and the bottle and pump dispenser have been very good. The list of ingredients includes some powerful, first class ingredients, but the product is very affordable. The texture is gel-like and not greasy.

The negative I have is that it doesn't moisturize enough for me. It's described as a "hydrating" eye gel, but I personally have to use another eye cream on top of this product. I don't necessarily like using two eye products on top of treatment serums. (I've been using Burt's Bees Renewal Smoothing Eye Cream to moisturize, and found I really like the level of moisture I get with it.) In terms of treatment impact, I haven't noticed anything significant.

With that said, it doesn't mean this product wouldn't work for someone else with different skin condition and concerns. I may go back to Timeless Skin Care's Hydrating Hyaluronic Acid + Matrixyl + Algae Eye Cream, which was a light-weight gel that was more moisturizing.

column6: Banana Boat Ultra Defense Sunscreen Lotion
column14: Banana Boat sunscreens contain a preservative called  Methylchloroisothiazolinone also called Methylisothiazolinone (MI), and about 10 other names like 2-Methyl-4-isothiazolin-3-one, 5-Chloro-2-methyl-4-isothiazolin-3-one., Acticide, Algucid, Amerstat 250, Euxyl K 100, Fennosan IT 21, Grotan TK2, Kathon, Kathon CG, Mergal K7, Metatin GT, Mitco CC 32 L.  I loved this sunscreen for the protection, unfortunately I and my children are allergic so i don't use it.  But different folks are allergic to different things.  In the UK I hear that 10% of the population is allergic to this ingredient.  It's also in cosmetic products for women: toners, cleansers, shampoos, moisturizers, make-up etc. So if you have a reaction to this, read labels on other products. I've heard it's called the Irish allergy because fair skinned folks are more allergic to this. Many sunscreens use something else for their preservative so look around.

column6: The Body Shop Hand Protector, Hemp, 3.3 Fluid Ounces (Packaging May Vary)
column13: An actual MIRACLE for my dry, split, cracked, painful fingers!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
column14:
This is the best handcream I have ever used. Let me tell you why you should trust me. I have extreme contact dermatitis and my hands are always dry, cracked, sometimes with little blisters. They are incredibly painful. I have tried every single hand cream from cheap to crazy expensive, from Walmart to L'Occitane, to medical grade to no avail. I started just wearing bandaids on each finger to keep the cracks from spreading.

One day I was totally fed up and remembered I had never tried The Body Shop Hemp Hand Protector. I ordered this one and used it. Day 1 my hands were at least 50% better with one application. Day 2 probably 75% better. Day 3 even better! Before the weeks end the cracks actually healed and the dry places were soft. I am now in what I consider "remission" from the dry cracked horrible fingers. Now for maintenance I use it once a day. I love it so much I ordered a second tube to keep in my purse. Just in case I feel the dryness coming I will have it with me. I don't know why it works so well but it does!

The ONLY cons I can see is the smell and packaging. I don't like it, but it's that good that I will overlook it. Eventually it goes away and is a million times more tolerable than dry cracked fingers. I'm not a fan of metal packaging but again, as long as it works I don't care about it.

I've been using this product for about a month now and here are my thoughts/experiences with it:

I read the reviews beforehand about the breakouts many experienced with the product and I suspect it was because they really pumped and slathered it on - so I made sure to Not do that. I used a pea size amount (not even) on my face( one pea sized amount for the lower part of my face and another for the top part)
I experienced no breakouts whatsoever and did see a difference - a little lightening of hyperpigmentation. Not completely gone but enough to know it's getting better

The downside of this product and perhaps it's because of the way I used it, is that my face would get a bit dry minutes after applying (maybe it absorbed too quickly idk) regardless I used the same amount morning and night.

It's not a bad cream..if you have skin that's not so dry I recommend this

What I absolutely DO NOT RECOMMEND is slathering this product on your face the same way you'd slather bbq sauce on some baby back ribs - of course your pores will be clogged and you will break out

If used on rougher surfaces, such as foot skin or any nails, will quickly dull the blade, causing rough skin tears instead of smooth, thin shaves. I find it especially great for my thumb corners and pointer finger sides - both areas tend to split easily. If I carefully and slowly cut the frayed skin, it keeps it from continued tears and splits. It can get a closer cut than a pair of nail-clippers, but you must move gently. I love mine so much, I'd rather use up the blades more quickly by using the tool for the rougher skin on either side of my toenails. I looked freshly pedicured at all times. :)  It's worth it to me to buy more tools as needed.

column6: Redken Cerafill Retaliate 2% Hair Regrowth Treatment for Women 2 Ounce
column14: My stylist had recommended that I begin using minoxidil after my last visit with her.  I have been using the Cerafill Defy line for sometime now, and Intraforce before that.  My hair has been slowly thinning for the last several years, and my stylist felt it was time for me to move on to minoxidil.  After about 2.5 - 3 weeks of using the topical treatment as directed, my hair began to fall out in very large quantities.  I continued to use the product for about another week, thinking that eventually the shedding would slow down after a couple of days.  It did not slow down.  I continued to lose so much hair that my scalp became even more visible than it was before I started the treatment.  I stopped using the product because I was afraid that if I didn't I would have no hair left on the top of my head.  It's been about a week since I stopped using the product and I'm still shedding.  The shedding I'm experiencing now is less than it was while I was using the product; however, it's still significantly more than any shedding that happened before I started.  I'm really disappointed.  I'm also really anxious about the possibility that, by using the minoxidil, I've created a situation where the hair I've lost won't grow back.  I would have never started using this product if I had known there was a possibility I would lose more hair.

column6: Restorative Eye CrÃ¨me, 15ml
column14:
I bought this eye cream when I received a spa visit as a birthday gift. I was wary of the recommendation b/c the product lines the spa carried were all unfamiliar to me, but since it was a spa that was alot "ritzier" than I'd ever been to, I believed at the time that I was just out of my normal product knowledge and it had to be good. I wasn't even aware at the time of the price of this eye cream since it was rolled into the total price of the visit. First, I noticed that the instructions say to use one pump of the product. One pump produces about double the size of a pea--way more than I need for both eyes. There is a generous amount in the bottle, so it should last awhile. The cream is a white, opaque, rich cream. Since I tend to get milia (the little white bumps that another reviewer described as "whiteheads that take a long time to go away") with very rich creams, I use it sparingly. (If you get these, Google "milia" so you'll know what they're all about.) The scent of this cream reminds me of my mom's generation's (she's about 75) hand cream--slightly chemical-ish, but it's not horribly strong. The feel of the cream was heavy, moisturizing, but way to rich for my skin.
This cream did moisturize my eye area, but did not do anything more than any other eye product I've used on my 50-year old skin that has some crow's feet, dark undereye circles, and the start of some eyelid crepiness.
I live in the humid, stiflingly hot South. So, I will probably reserve this cream to use only at night (it makes too much of an oil slick on my eye area to be able to wear eye makeup) and only in the winter when I need a little more moisture.
I have regularly used less expensive products (Murad, Exuvience, Estee Lauder, etc.) that contain effective ingredients that are more suited to my skin and will go back to those.

column13: If you're looking for a beautiful incense for any occasion, you've found it.
column14:
HEM's "The Moon" is a gorgeous blend of perfumes, resins, and the subtle scent of milk and honey. It's a dreamy smell that juxtapositions delicate and bold, much like the moon itself when seen from afar and up close. In terms of using this for relaxation and meditation, it beckons your mind into a deep state.

One thing I can say about this meditation compared to the others I use (mostly Shoyeido, a Japanese incense company) is that this gets quickly overpowering without proper ventilation. Of course, you should always have a window open when burning incense or any kind of resins/herbs, but this one especially needs a window and door open, especially if burning in a small room. This is one small con that can be fixed easily.

If you have 8ish dollars to spend, definitely treat yourself to this incense! It keeps guests coming back, gets your mind centered, and lets anything spiritual manifest.

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength 1 Each
column13: Removes the dye, colour is almost the same as before but not quite
column14:
This stuff works nearly as well as it claims to. I had medium brown hair with highlights and tried to dye it a dark brown, but it came out utterly black. I didn't find out about Color Oops until two months later, and gave it a shot anyway. It stripped the colour out even after two months! What I got in the end was a brassier version of what I had before, which was fine because it was light enough to dye it.
Important tips:
-It will NOT remove fake colours like green, pink, blue, etc. It only removes regular colours and it says so in the directions.
-It can only work if you dyed your hair darker and want the light colour back. All it does is remove the dye, it can't restore colour to hair that was stripped with bleach or highlights, so don't bother unless you accidentally dyed it too dark.
-The smell is very strong and it will take days to rinse out.
-Even though it isn't bleach, it will dry out your hair so have some reparative conditioner to use after.
-If you want to dye it again right after, you need to buy a lighter shade than normal. The hair will be porous and will soak up a huge amount of dye, meaning you will end up with too-dark hair all over again if you aren't careful about getting a light enough colour.
-The mixture is thin, my hair only goes to my chin and I still used the whole bottle. You might need two bottles, or I have heard of other people mixing in a bit of shampoo to thicken it but I didn't take the risk myself so I'm not sure.
-The dye may have permanently stripped some colour and made it slightly orange, so it's good to have a new dye on hand just in case.

column14: For me it was just ok. I've had 'mermaid' colored hair for about two years now so any color I put in is not new or fresh for the first time other than where it gets applied to new growth. Generally for me that makes it easier as far as getting color to stay because I've built it up over time. With this I didn't feel it performed like everybody keeps saying it does. The green I used previously was a different brand and much more green than blue. It was easy to see when this was wearing out because the blue green was gone and the faded grassier green shade I had before coloring with this dye was more visible. I didn't rinse in vinegar like some people do or throw any of the extras on, just followed the directions on the package. For reference I only wash and condition in very cold water and wash my hair twice a week. Within a couple of weeks this was mostly out of my hair. Considering the price and the fact that I had to use more than one bottle to cover my medium length hair, I wouldn't purchase again. The packaging also makes it difficult to get all of the color out of the hard plastic bottle which is also frustrating. The color is true to the bottle and is pretty, but I wouldn't purchase again.

column6: L'Oreal Paris Extra-Volume Collagen Mascara, 0.34-Fluid Ounce
column13: may irritate sensitive eyes; otherwise a good, basic mascara
column14:
I'm basically happy with this. Some things I particularly like:

*The color. This really is quite a nice black. I have sort of dark eyelashes but this shows up.

*Removability. This actually comes off without scrubbing or leaving me with raccoon eyes the next morning. I have been using some Acure argan oil facial wipes (the latest product of this sort I've tried) to remove it and those have been working well.

*Brush. I am finding this works fairly well and I have not been getting mascara all over my face (other brush designs sometimes make application messier).

*Formula performance. Is not thick or clumpy. Just the right amount sticks to the brush.

Despite the good qualities, this isn't the mascara for me, though. It promises extreme volume and, while there is definitely a volume boost, it's only a little above average for me. Also, for what it's worth, this is not a vegan product (contains collagen and hyaluronic acid, both of which come from animal sources).

But, most importantly, it irritates my eyes quite a bit. I actually had to leave work early yesterday to go home and deal with the eye irritation. (I wear contact lenses and have sensitive eyes.)

Overall, a solid mascara if your eyes are not sensitive. Just not as dramatic as the package claims. 2.5 stars.

column6: ORGANIC EVENING PRIMROSE OIL. 100% Pure / Natural / Undiluted / Unrefined /Certified Organic/ Cold Pressed Carrier Oil. Rich antioxidant to rejuvenate and moisturize the skin and hair. 0.5 Fl.oz.- 15 ml. by Botanical Beauty
column13: Awesome carrier oil! Mix it with Jojoba for an awesome hair conditioner!
column14:
I'm an avid user of essential oils which means that I'm always on the lookout for new oils/carrier oils so I can mix up new concoctions. I'm always mixing up new face washes, hair conditioners, moisturizers, and trying out new concoctions.

I've been using this oil mixed with jojoba for hair conditioner and I gotta say it has made my hair look super healthy and has made it very soft. I've also heard its very good for skin aliments so the next time I get an acne breakout I will definitely be giving it a try.

Overall, this seems like a really great carrier oil. I prefer this just slightly over coconut oil because it doesn't seem to feel as greasy nor does it smell as much.

I was able to snag a discount in exchange for testing it out and leaving a review. Having said that, I take reviews seriously and I'm under no obligation to leave a good review. The opinions above are my own and my honest opinion is that this is a fantastic carrier oil for anyones essential oil collection!

column14:

* Came 1day before predicted date!
*Works wonders also and doesn't fry my hair!
*The price is a total steal! But it truly is one of those "you get what you pay for" type of deals. Though it works wonders for most hair/most people just as good as a top dollar flat iron it's older generation of flat iron compared to what you see today with modernized flat irons.
* The on and off is a slideable switch on the inside by the plates as so is the temperature dial. And a design flaw for the most because the dial is small and could be made bigger.
*The "heating up" light(red) & "ready to use" light(green) work fine.
*The end of the cord to plug into the wall is like one you'd see on your hair dryer. I call it a mini breaker switch.
*It's all black, of course. The travel sleeve is soft and is red. In great condition!
*The glove is literally a black, light duty garden glove.
*And the hair oil is a sample size. Yes, it SMALL.

Other than the flaws described in the overview, it's overall a great product!

column13: A beneficial toner that doesn't run out between your fingers
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Orange blossom water and witch hazel
~ Feel during application: Just like a liquid toner, but thicker so it doesnâ€™t run out between your fingers. This thicker formulation is genius!
~ Feel after absorption: Powdery-smooth, clean, and matte.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should work for all. No irritation of my sensitive, oily skin.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 2oz plastic squeeze bottle with press-open cap.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Reduces redness, firms skin tone.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Itâ€™s a toner, not intended to stand on its own. But unlike many toners, this contains a ton of beneficial ingredients for healing and anti-aging. Itâ€™s actively good for your skin and would be an excellent addition to your regimen.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

As a product tester I received this free or virtually so for evaluation and review. This does NOT mean this is a fake review. I was not paid for my review, or given any incentive or reward for a positive review. If you don't believe me, click my profile to see the poor reviews I've given bad products. My job is to give an honest opinion, not help the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column6: Castor Oil - Jamaican Black - 8 oz - Stimulate Hair Growth
column14: Listen ladies, this stuff is the truth! I bought this JBCO to help fill in my thinning edges. Initially I was massaging my edges with the oil in the morning and at night. I think after about a week or so I noticed the growth. Because I had previously dyed my hair a light brown color it was quite easy to see my dark brown/black new growth. I was so excited. I have been using the JBCO now for about maybe 5 or 6 weeks. Before using this product my edges never seemed to grow..ever. As a matter of fact, before using the oil on my edges I did have new growth on my scalp hair but none around my edges...seriously. Now it's growing in nice in thick (well thick for me 'cause I have fine hair). I'm in the process of doing a relaxer stretch (considering going natural) so I have been mixing the JBCO with other oils to apply to my scalp every other day and right now I have almost 2 inches of new growth. I feel that I have reasonably fast growing hair, but almost 2 inches of hair in...let's see...almost 2 1/2 months (this is also counting time before using JBCO). Never has that happened! My last relaxer was mid May, I started using the JBCO on my scalp maybe the end of June/beginning of July. I started off with just the edges. Now just to clarify, before using on my scalp I already had some new growth, but it really seem like the JBCO boosted growth. But at the same time I am also using the "greenhouse effect" along with other growth theories in my regimen as well. But anyway ladies, before I get to rambling like some crazy person, the point is I love this stuff and it does work and I wish you much success on your hair journey!!!

column6: Panasonic ES2216PC Womenâ€™s Close Curves Cordless Wet / Dry Electric Shaver New
column13: Are you on your way out for a pedicure? Grab this baby, first!
column14: I'm a razor person, but this product is fantastic for touch-ups! I've only used it dry, and after using it, my leg hair is invisible to the naked eye, which is my intention. I always seem to forget I have something going on at the last minute, and I don't want visible hair on display. All shavers I've ever tried leave a small amount of stubble that you can feel by hand, and this shaver is the same, but only slightly so. And again, no visible hair. It's easy enough to clean and has it's own little brush. I haven't had any pinching or hair tugging, in part I think because I always pull my skin taught so the blades can do their job making precision cuts. I even feel confident that if I used this in the shower, I'd be able to comfortably press more firmly for a very close shave. I'll update my review if that's not the case!

column13: Beautiful pair of earrings for a child or an adult
column14:
When I pulled these earrings out of the bag my daughter gasped with excitement. Although I didn't intend for them to be hers I did give them to her. She was so excited. These are just as pretty in person as they are on in the pictures if not prettier. They are shiny and bright with the small center stone. They are small enough to be a perfect size for a little girl but they are big enough for a woman to wear them as well. They would look great for bridesmaids/flower-girls with updos. They are well made the post is very sturdy. The back closes tight so they will not fall off during the day. They come in a velvet pouch which protects them during shipping and storage. The pouch also makes them a beautiful for gifts. I love the design and although it is intended to be a four leaf clover it looks a lot like a butterfly as well. I let my daugther call them what she wanted.
I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest opinion but the opinion expressed is all my own.

column6: Qianse LOVE You Forever Lettering Double Heart Elegant Crystal Pendant Necklace, Love Confession
column14:
Two hearts, fitting one inside the other. The largest heart (approximately 5/8" high) has tiny crystals embedded all around its edge. The inner heart (approximately 1/2" high) has the words "LOVE YOU FOREVER" engraved around the outer edge. The chain (also sterling silver) is approximately 18" long.

Dainty, simple yet complex and meaningful are all words I would use to describe this necklace. Would I recommend this to others? Absolutely! In my opinion it is good value and would also make a beautiful gift.

It is important to note that there are two DIFFERENT necklaces available under the same listing. One is 925 sterling silver (yes, this is stamped on the hearts and chain) and the other (cheaper) is white gold plated. This review is on the sterling silver double heart necklace. Necklace comes in a bag that is folded to prevent the chain entangling in itself. The necklace and bag are in a quality gift box. Product provided in exchange for an honest review. Thanks, Liz

column14:
I bought this ring in yellow gold and I have to say that it is one of the best purchases I've made. It's a beautiful product, is durable and looks exactly like the real thing. I have been asked multiple times how much I love this ring by people looking to purchase the real thing. The only way to know the difference would be to hold the ring as the weight of real gold is unmistakeable. The engravings are identical to the real love ring.
I know that replicas of real products are usually very obviously fake looking but this ring and the matching bracelet are the exception. With the engravings and the flawless craftsmanship, it's hard to tell a difference between the fake and the real thing.
I have a friend who was gifted with the real love ring by her boyfriend and she was floored by the lack of difference in the rings.
This is a beautiful yet understated ring and is a fantastic dupe for the real thing. Buy it!
I shouldn't forget to mention the customer service. Fast response when contacted, and I received the ring 8 days after I purchased it. Awesome!

column13: This is now my favorite ring ever
column14:
This is now my favorite ring ever. First off, most of the things I own are Gold and black. It is, in my opinion the classiest color scheme there is. Second the comfort fit that this ring has is phenomenal. All of my other rings can get uncomfortable after wearing them for prolonged periods of time because of the edged part of the inside of the ring, they will dig in as the rings move around. Not this ring though. the inside part is curved slightly to prevent the uncomfortable rubbing. For it's size the ring is heavy, I'm assuming because it is tungsten. seems very durable. After wearing it for a couple days I've gotten a lot of compliments on it. I love the way it looks and feels on my hand.
I received a discount on this item in exchange for giving it an honest review.

column13: It has a shiny look to the leather but I bent it and twisted until I wore it down to the way I liked it. After cutting and drill
column14:
The size was a bit off from 25 inches or at least the one I got, but they were more than willing to allow me to return it for another one. It has a shiny look to the leather but I bent it and twisted until I wore it down to the way I liked it. After cutting and drilling out the other leather and adjusting it to the size that fit me most comfortably I can say without a doubt this is a amazing necklace. It definitely feels like it will last a long time and has nice quality metal. The only thing I dislike it that its fairly easy to bend back and forth. I was hoping for a different way to change out pendants but seeing as how I like it just the way it is I don't have to worry about that.

In the end though out of all the things I had to do to it, it made it feel that much better to me and this will without a doubt be my go to necklace for many years to come. Thanks Bico!

column6: Womens Pink Haven Camo Ring ON SALE NOW, 6mm comfort fit Pink Camo Rings, Camo Wedding Rings for Women LIFETIME WARRANTY
column14:
I love that this is a little rugged, but still has that girly charm to it. The splash of pink lets you know right away it is a feminine ring, and it shows your own personal style.

The ring is a little more heavy then a basic band, but not so much that it feels weighted down. It is a little more wide than I am used to as well, but the absence of a setting, keeps it from being bothersome. It spins easily and moves freely and has a nice smooth finish on the inside too. This makes the rings super easy to glide on and off, and doesn't seem to get stuck as easily if you suffer from swollen fingers at the end of a hard day.

This is a great band to show your own personal style. The quality means it works perfectly as a wedding band, a holiday or birthday gift, for a graduation, or just to wear every day. This is a nice choice for the camo fan who wants to wear their ring all the time, but doesn't want it to catch on anything while working or playing. The thin edging of silver adds a bit of flair to the pattern, and it looks great with all my camo accessories too. I love this ring and would love to see them in every color.

*I received a sample item in exchange for my honest opinions.
